entries.description: A company or fund that gathers capital from a number of investors to create a pool of money that is then re-invested into stocks, bonds and other assets.

entries.name: schema:InvestmentOrDeposit
entries.description: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.

entries.name: schema:InviteAction
entries.description: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

entries.name: schema:Invoice
entries.description: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

entries.name: schema:ItemAvailability
entries.description: A list of possible product availability options.

entries.name: schema:ItemList
entries.description: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

entries.name: schema:ItemListOrderType
entries.description: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

entries.name: schema:ItemPage
entries.description: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.

entries.name: schema:JewelryStore
entries.description: A jewelry store.

entries.name: schema:JobPosting
entries.description: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

entries.name: schema:JoinAction
entries.description:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.

entries.name: schema:Joint
entries.description: The anatomical location at which two or more bones make contact.

entries.name: schema:LakeBodyOfWater
entries.description: A lake (for example, Lake Pontrachain).

entries.name: schema:Landform
entries.description: A landform or physical feature.  Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

entries.name: schema:LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings
entries.description: An historical landmark or building.

entries.name: schema:Language
entries.description: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in [BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) can be used via the [[alternateName]] property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using [[ComputerLanguage]].

entries.name: schema:LearningResource
entries.description:
The LearningResource type can be used to indicate [[CreativeWork]]s (whether physical or digital) that have a particular and explicit orientation towards learning, education, skill acquisition, and other educational purposes.

[[LearningResource]] is expected to be used as an addition to a primary type such as [[Book]], [[VideoObject]], [[Product]] etc.

[[EducationEvent]] serves a similar purpose for event-like things (e.g. a [[Trip]]). A [[LearningResource]] may be created as a result of an [[EducationEvent]], for example by recording one.

entries.name: schema:LeaveAction
entries.description:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: The antonym of LeaveAction.
* [[UnRegisterAction]]: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.

entries.name: schema:LegalForceStatus
entries.description: A list of possible statuses for the legal force of a legislation.

entries.name: schema:LegalService
entries.description: A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

entries.name: schema:LegalValueLevel
entries.description: A list of possible levels for the legal validity of a legislation.

entries.name: schema:Legislation
entries.description: A legal document such as an act, decree, bill, etc. (enforceable or not) or a component of a legal act (like an article).

entries.name: schema:LegislationObject
entries.description: A specific object or file containing a Legislation. Note that the same Legislation can be published in multiple files. For example, a digitally signed PDF, a plain PDF and an HTML version.

entries.name: schema:LegislativeBuilding
entries.description: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

entries.name: schema:LendAction
entries.description:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Related actions:

* [[BorrowAction]]: Reciprocal of LendAction.

entries.name: schema:Library
entries.description: A library.

entries.name: schema:LibrarySystem
entries.description: A [[LibrarySystem]] is a collaborative system amongst several libraries.

entries.name: schema:LifestyleModification
entries.description: A process of care involving exercise, changes to diet, fitness routines, and other lifestyle changes aimed at improving a health condition.

entries.name: schema:Ligament
entries.description: A short band of tough, flexible, fibrous connective tissue that functions to connect multiple bones, cartilages, and structurally support joints.

entries.name: schema:LikeAction
entries.description: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

entries.name: schema:LinkRole
entries.description: A Role that represents a Web link, e.g. as expressed via the 'url' property. Its linkRelationship property can indicate URL-based and plain textual link types, e.g. those in IANA link registry or others such as 'amphtml'. This structure provides a placeholder where details from HTML's link element can be represented outside of HTML, e.g. in JSON-LD feeds.

entries.name: schema:LiquorStore
entries.description: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

entries.name: schema:ListItem
entries.description: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

entries.name: schema:ListenAction
entries.description: The act of consuming audio content.

entries.name: schema:LiteraryEvent
entries.description: Event type: Literary event.

entries.name: schema:LiveBlogPosting
entries.description: A [[LiveBlogPosting]] is a [[BlogPosting]] intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.

entries.name: schema:LoanOrCredit
entries.description: A financial product for the loaning of an amount of money, or line of credit, under agreed terms and charges.

entries.name: schema:LocalBusiness
entries.description: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

entries.name: schema:LocationFeatureSpecification
entries.description: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.

entries.name: schema:Locksmith
entries.description: A locksmith.

entries.name: schema:LodgingBusiness
entries.description: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

entries.name: schema:LodgingReservation
entries.description: A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

entries.name: schema:LoginAction
entries.description: The action of logging into a device or application.

entries.name: schema:LoseAction
entries.description: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

entries.name: schema:LymphaticVessel
entries.description: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries lymph fluid unidirectionally toward the heart.

entries.name: schema:Manuscript
entries.description: A book, document, or piece of music written by hand rather than typed or printed.

entries.name: schema:Map
entries.description: A map.

entries.name: schema:MapCategoryType
entries.description: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

entries.name: schema:MarryAction
entries.description: The act of marrying a person.

entries.name: schema:Mass
entries.description: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

entries.name: schema:MathSolver
entries.description: A math solver which is capable of solving a subset of mathematical problems.

entries.name: schema:MaximumDoseSchedule
entries.description: The maximum dosing schedule considered safe for a drug or supplement as recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

entries.name: schema:MeasurementMethodEnum
entries.description: Enumeration(s) for use with [[measurementMethod]].

entries.name: schema:MeasurementTypeEnumeration
entries.description: Enumeration of common measurement types (or dimensions), for example "chest" for a person, "inseam" for pants, "gauge" for screws, or "wheel" for bicycles.

entries.name: schema:MediaEnumeration
entries.description: MediaEnumeration enumerations are lists of codes, labels etc. useful for describing media objects. They may be reflections of externally developed lists, or created at schema.org, or a combination.

entries.name: schema:MediaGallery
entries.description: Web page type: Media gallery page. A mixed-media page that can contain media such as images, videos, and other multimedia.

entries.name: schema:MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration
entries.description: Codes for use with the [[mediaAuthenticityCategory]] property, indicating the authenticity of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared). In general these codes are not mutually exclusive, although some combinations (such as 'original' versus 'transformed', 'edited' and 'staged') would be contradictory if applied in the same [[MediaReview]]. Note that the application of these codes is with regard to a piece of media shared or published in a particular context.

entries.name: schema:MediaObject
entries.description: A media object, such as an image, video, audio, or text object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

entries.name: schema:MediaReview
entries.description:
A [[MediaReview]] is a more specialized form of Review dedicated to the evaluation of media content online, typically in the context of fact-checking and misinformation.
    For more general reviews of media in the broader sense, use [[UserReview]], [[CriticReview]] or other [[Review]] types. This definition is
    a work in progress. While the [[MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration]] list reflects significant community review amongst fact-checkers and others working
    to combat misinformation, the specific structures for representing media objects, their versions and publication context, are still evolving. Similarly, best practices for the relationship between [[MediaReview]] and [[ClaimReview]] markup have not yet been finalized.

entries.name: schema:MediaReviewItem
entries.description: Represents an item or group of closely related items treated as a unit for the sake of evaluation in a [[MediaReview]]. Authorship etc. apply to the items rather than to the curation/grouping or reviewing party.

entries.name: schema:MediaSubscription
entries.description: A subscription which allows a user to access media including audio, video, books, etc.

entries.name: schema:MedicalAudience
entries.description: Target audiences for medical web pages.

entries.name: schema:MedicalAudienceType
entries.description: Target audiences types for medical web pages. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalBusiness
entries.description: A particular physical or virtual business of an organization for medical purposes. Examples of MedicalBusiness include different businesses run by health professionals.

entries.name: schema:MedicalCause
entries.description: The causative agent(s) that are responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in a medical condition, symptom or sign. In this schema, unless otherwise specified this is meant to be the proximate cause of the medical condition, symptom or sign. The proximate cause is defined as the causative agent that most directly results in the medical condition, symptom or sign. For example, the HIV virus could be considered a cause of AIDS. Or in a diagnostic context, if a patient fell and sustained a hip fracture and two days later sustained a pulmonary embolism which eventuated in a cardiac arrest, the cause of the cardiac arrest (the proximate cause) would be the pulmonary embolism and not the fall. Medical causes can include cardiovascular, chemical, dermatologic, endocrine, environmental, gastroenterologic, genetic, hematologic, gynecologic, iatrogenic, infectious, musculoskeletal, neurologic, nutritional, obstetric, oncologic, otolaryngologic, pharmacologic, psychiatric, pulmonary, renal, rheumatologic, toxic, traumatic, or urologic causes; medical conditions can be causes as well.

entries.name: schema:MedicalClinic
entries.description: A facility, often associated with a hospital or medical school, that is devoted to the specific diagnosis and/or healthcare. Previously limited to outpatients but with evolution it may be open to inpatients as well.

entries.name: schema:MedicalCode
entries.description: A code for a medical entity.

entries.name: schema:MedicalCondition
entries.description: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

entries.name: schema:MedicalConditionStage
entries.description: A stage of a medical condition, such as 'Stage IIIa'.

entries.name: schema:MedicalContraindication
entries.description: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

entries.name: schema:MedicalDevice
entries.description: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

entries.name: schema:MedicalDevicePurpose
entries.description: Categories of medical devices, organized by the purpose or intended use of the device.

entries.name: schema:MedicalEntity
entries.description: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

entries.name: schema:MedicalEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerations related to health and the practice of medicine: A concept that is used to attribute a quality to another concept, as a qualifier, a collection of items or a listing of all of the elements of a set in medicine practice.

entries.name: schema:MedicalEvidenceLevel
entries.description: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalGuideline
entries.description: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

entries.name: schema:MedicalGuidelineContraindication
entries.description: A guideline contraindication that designates a process as harmful and where quality of the data supporting the contraindication is sound.

entries.name: schema:MedicalGuidelineRecommendation
entries.description: A guideline recommendation that is regarded as efficacious and where quality of the data supporting the recommendation is sound.

entries.name: schema:MedicalImagingTechnique
entries.description: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalIndication
entries.description: A condition or factor that indicates use of a medical therapy, including signs, symptoms, risk factors, anatomical states, etc.

entries.name: schema:MedicalIntangible
entries.description: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things in the medical space.

entries.name: schema:MedicalObservationalStudy
entries.description: An observational study is a type of medical study that attempts to infer the possible effect of a treatment through observation of a cohort of subjects over a period of time. In an observational study, the assignment of subjects into treatment groups versus control groups is outside the control of the investigator. This is in contrast with controlled studies, such as the randomized controlled trials represented by MedicalTrial, where each subject is randomly assigned to a treatment group or a control group before the start of the treatment.

entries.name: schema:MedicalObservationalStudyDesign
entries.description: Design models for observational medical studies. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalOrganization
entries.description: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.

entries.name: schema:MedicalProcedure
entries.description: A process of care used in either a diagnostic, therapeutic, preventive or palliative capacity that relies on invasive (surgical), non-invasive, or other techniques.

entries.name: schema:MedicalProcedureType
entries.description: An enumeration that describes different types of medical procedures.

entries.name: schema:MedicalRiskCalculator
entries.description: A complex mathematical calculation requiring an online calculator, used to assess prognosis. Note: use the url property of Thing to record any URLs for online calculators.

entries.name: schema:MedicalRiskEstimator
entries.description: Any rule set or interactive tool for estimating the risk of developing a complication or condition.

entries.name: schema:MedicalRiskFactor
entries.description: A risk factor is anything that increases a person's likelihood of developing or contracting a disease, medical condition, or complication.

entries.name: schema:MedicalRiskScore
entries.description: A simple system that adds up the number of risk factors to yield a score that is associated with prognosis, e.g. CHAD score, TIMI risk score.

entries.name: schema:MedicalScholarlyArticle
entries.description: A scholarly article in the medical domain.

entries.name: schema:MedicalSign
entries.description: Any physical manifestation of a person's medical condition discoverable by objective diagnostic tests or physical examination.

entries.name: schema:MedicalSignOrSymptom
entries.description: Any feature associated or not with a medical condition. In medicine a symptom is generally subjective while a sign is objective.

entries.name: schema:MedicalSpecialty
entries.description: Any specific branch of medical science or practice. Medical specialities include clinical specialties that pertain to particular organ systems and their respective disease states, as well as allied health specialties. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalStudy
entries.description: A medical study is an umbrella type covering all kinds of research studies relating to human medicine or health, including observational studies and interventional trials and registries, randomized, controlled or not. When the specific type of study is known, use one of the extensions of this type, such as MedicalTrial or MedicalObservationalStudy. Also, note that this type should be used to mark up data that describes the study itself; to tag an article that publishes the results of a study, use MedicalScholarlyArticle. Note: use the code property of MedicalEntity to store study IDs, e.g. clinicaltrials.gov ID.

entries.name: schema:MedicalStudyStatus
entries.description: The status of a medical study. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalSymptom
entries.description: Any complaint sensed and expressed by the patient (therefore defined as subjective)  like stomachache, lower-back pain, or fatigue.

entries.name: schema:MedicalTest
entries.description: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

entries.name: schema:MedicalTestPanel
entries.description: Any collection of tests commonly ordered together.

entries.name: schema:MedicalTherapy
entries.description: Any medical intervention designed to prevent, treat, and cure human diseases and medical conditions, including both curative and palliative therapies. Medical therapies are typically processes of care relying upon pharmacotherapy, behavioral therapy, supportive therapy (with fluid or nutrition for example), or detoxification (e.g. hemodialysis) aimed at improving or preventing a health condition.

entries.name: schema:MedicalTrial
entries.description: A medical trial is a type of medical study that uses a scientific process to compare the safety and efficacy of medical therapies or medical procedures. In general, medical trials are controlled and subjects are allocated at random to the different treatment and/or control groups.

entries.name: schema:MedicalTrialDesign
entries.description: Design models for medical trials. Enumerated type.

entries.name: schema:MedicalWebPage
entries.description: A web page that provides medical information.

entries.name: schema:MedicineSystem
entries.description: Systems of medical practice.

entries.name: schema:MeetingRoom
entries.description:
A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

entries.name: schema:MemberProgram
entries.description: A MemberProgram defines a loyalty (or membership) program that provides its members with certain benefits, for example better pricing, free shipping or returns, or the ability to earn loyalty points. Member programs may have multiple tiers, for example silver and gold members, each with different benefits.

entries.name: schema:MemberProgramTier
entries.description: A MemberProgramTier specifies a tier under a loyalty (member) program, for example "gold".

entries.name: schema:MensClothingStore
entries.description: A men's clothing store.

entries.name: schema:Menu
entries.description: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.

entries.name: schema:MenuItem
entries.description: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.

entries.name: schema:MenuSection
entries.description: A sub-grouping of food or drink items in a menu. E.g. courses (such as 'Dinner', 'Breakfast', etc.), specific type of dishes (such as 'Meat', 'Vegan', 'Drinks', etc.), or some other classification made by the menu provider.

entries.name: schema:MerchantReturnEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates several kinds of product return policies.

entries.name: schema:MerchantReturnPolicy
entries.description: A MerchantReturnPolicy provides information about product return policies associated with an [[Organization]], [[Product]], or [[Offer]].

entries.name: schema:MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride
entries.description: A seasonal override of a return policy, for example used for holidays.

entries.name: schema:Message
entries.description: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.

entries.name: schema:MiddleSchool
entries.description: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).

entries.name: schema:MobileApplication
entries.description: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.

entries.name: schema:MobilePhoneStore
entries.description: A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.

entries.name: schema:MolecularEntity
entries.description: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

entries.name: schema:MonetaryAmount
entries.description: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between 1,000 and 1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use [[PriceSpecification]] Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.

entries.name: schema:MonetaryAmountDistribution
entries.description: A statistical distribution of monetary amounts.

entries.name: schema:MonetaryGrant
entries.description: A monetary grant.

entries.name: schema:MoneyTransfer
entries.description: The act of transferring money from one place to another place. This may occur electronically or physically.

entries.name: schema:MortgageLoan
entries.description: A loan in which property or real estate is used as collateral. (A loan securitized against some real estate.)

entries.name: schema:Mosque
entries.description: A mosque.

entries.name: schema:Motel
entries.description:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

entries.name: schema:Motorcycle
entries.description: A motorcycle or motorbike is a single-track, two-wheeled motor vehicle.

entries.name: schema:MotorcycleDealer
entries.description: A motorcycle dealer.

entries.name: schema:MotorcycleRepair
entries.description: A motorcycle repair shop.

entries.name: schema:MotorizedBicycle
entries.description: A motorized bicycle is a bicycle with an attached motor used to power the vehicle, or to assist with pedaling.

entries.name: schema:Mountain
entries.description: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

entries.name: schema:MoveAction
entries.description:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

* [[TransferAction]]: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

entries.name: schema:Movie
entries.description: A movie.

entries.name: schema:MovieClip
entries.description: A short segment/part of a movie.

entries.name: schema:MovieRentalStore
entries.description: A movie rental store.

entries.name: schema:MovieSeries
entries.description: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

entries.name: schema:MovieTheater
entries.description: A movie theater.

entries.name: schema:MovingCompany
entries.description: A moving company.

entries.name: schema:Muscle
entries.description: A muscle is an anatomical structure consisting of a contractile form of tissue that animals use to effect movement.

entries.name: schema:Museum
entries.description: A museum.

entries.name: schema:MusicAlbum
entries.description: A collection of music tracks.

entries.name: schema:MusicAlbumProductionType
entries.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

entries.name: schema:MusicAlbumReleaseType
entries.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

entries.name: schema:MusicComposition
entries.description: A musical composition.

entries.name: schema:MusicEvent
entries.description: Event type: Music event.

entries.name: schema:MusicGroup
entries.description: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

entries.name: schema:MusicPlaylist
entries.description: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

entries.name: schema:MusicRecording
entries.description: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

entries.name: schema:MusicRelease
entries.description: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

entries.name: schema:MusicReleaseFormatType
entries.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

entries.name: schema:MusicStore
entries.description: A music store.

entries.name: schema:MusicVenue
entries.description: A music venue.

entries.name: schema:MusicVideoObject
entries.description: A music video file.

entries.name: schema:NGO
entries.description: Organization: Non-governmental Organization.

entries.name: schema:NLNonprofitType
entries.description: NLNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the Netherlands.

entries.name: schema:NailSalon
entries.description: A nail salon.

entries.name: schema:Nerve
entries.description: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

entries.name: schema:NewsArticle
entries.description:
A NewsArticle is an article whose content reports news, or provides background context and supporting materials for understanding the news.

A more detailed overview of [schema.org News markup](/docs/news.html) is also available.

entries.name: schema:NewsMediaOrganization
entries.description: A News/Media organization such as a newspaper or TV station.

entries.name: schema:Newspaper
entries.description: A publication containing information about varied topics that are pertinent to general information, a geographic area, or a specific subject matter (i.e. business, culture, education). Often published daily.

entries.name: schema:NightClub
entries.description: A nightclub or discotheque.

entries.name: schema:NonprofitType
entries.description: NonprofitType enumerates several kinds of official non-profit types of which a non-profit organization can be.

entries.name: schema:Notary
entries.description: A notary.

entries.name: schema:NoteDigitalDocument
entries.description: A file containing a note, primarily for the author.

entries.name: schema:Number
entries.description:
Data type: Number.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

entries.name: schema:NutritionInformation
entries.description: Nutritional information about the recipe.

entries.name: schema:Observation
entries.description:
Instances of the class [[Observation]] are used to specify observations about an entity at a particular time. The principal properties of an [[Observation]] are [[observationAbout]], [[measuredProperty]], [[statType]], [[value] and [[observationDate]]  and [[measuredProperty]]. Some but not all Observations represent a [[QuantitativeValue]]. Quantitative observations can be about a [[StatisticalVariable]], which is an abstract specification about which we can make observations that are grounded at a particular location and time.

Observations can also encode a subset of simple RDF-like statements (its observationAbout, a StatisticalVariable, defining the measuredPoperty; its observationAbout property indicating the entity the statement is about, and [[value]] )

In the context of a quantitative knowledge graph, typical properties could include [[measuredProperty]], [[observationAbout]], [[observationDate]], [[value]], [[unitCode]], [[unitText]], [[measurementMethod]].

entries.name: schema:Occupation
entries.description: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

entries.name: schema:OccupationalExperienceRequirements
entries.description: Indicates employment-related experience requirements, e.g. [[monthsOfExperience]].

entries.name: schema:OccupationalTherapy
entries.description: A treatment of people with physical, emotional, or social problems, using purposeful activity to help them overcome or learn to deal with their problems.

entries.name: schema:OceanBodyOfWater
entries.description: An ocean (for example, the Pacific).

entries.name: schema:Offer
entries.description:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service  for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

Note: As the [[businessFunction]] property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.

For [GTIN](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin)-related fields, see [Check Digit calculator](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/support/check_digit_calculator) and [validation guide](http://www.gs1us.org/resources/standards/gtin-validation-guide) from [GS1](http://www.gs1.org/).

entries.name: schema:OfferCatalog
entries.description: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

entries.name: schema:OfferForLease
entries.description:
An [[OfferForLease]] in Schema.org represents an [[Offer]] to lease out something, i.e. an [[Offer]] whose
  [[businessFunction]] is [lease out](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#LeaseOut.). See [Good Relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodRelations) for
  background on the underlying concepts.

entries.name: schema:OfferForPurchase
entries.description:
An [[OfferForPurchase]] in Schema.org represents an [[Offer]] to sell something, i.e. an [[Offer]] whose
  [[businessFunction]] is [sell](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.). See [Good Relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodRelations) for
  background on the underlying concepts.

entries.name: schema:OfferItemCondition
entries.description: A list of possible conditions for the item.

entries.name: schema:OfferShippingDetails
entries.description:
OfferShippingDetails represents information about shipping destinations.

Multiple of these entities can be used to represent different shipping rates for different destinations:

One entity for Alaska/Hawaii. A different one for continental US. A different one for all France.

Multiple of these entities can be used to represent different shipping costs and delivery times.

Two entities that are identical but differ in rate and time:

E.g. Cheaper and slower: $5 in 5-7 days
or Fast and expensive: $15 in 1-2 days.

entries.name: schema:OfficeEquipmentStore
entries.description: An office equipment store.

entries.name: schema:OnDemandEvent
entries.description: A publication event, e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

entries.name: schema:OnlineBusiness
entries.description: A particular online business, either standalone or the online part of a broader organization. Examples include an eCommerce site, an online travel booking site, an online learning site, an online logistics and shipping provider, an online (virtual) doctor, etc.

entries.name: schema:OnlineMarketplace
entries.description: An eCommerce marketplace.

entries.name: schema:OnlineStore
entries.description: An eCommerce site.

entries.name: schema:OpeningHoursSpecification
entries.description:
A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.


The place is __open__ if the [[opens]] property is specified, and __closed__ otherwise.

If the value for the [[closes]] property is less than the value for the [[opens]] property then the hour range is assumed to span over the next day.

entries.name: schema:OperatingSystem
entries.description: System software that manages computer hardware and software resources, and provides common services for computer programs.

entries.name: schema:OpinionNewsArticle
entries.description: An [[OpinionNewsArticle]] is a [[NewsArticle]] that primarily expresses opinions rather than journalistic reporting of news and events. For example, a [[NewsArticle]] consisting of a column or [[Blog]]/[[BlogPosting]] entry in the Opinions section of a news publication.

entries.name: schema:Optician
entries.description: A store that sells reading glasses and similar devices for improving vision.

entries.name: schema:Order
entries.description: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

entries.name: schema:OrderAction
entries.description: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

entries.name: schema:OrderItem
entries.description: An order item is a line of an order. It includes the quantity and shipping details of a bought offer.

entries.name: schema:OrderStatus
entries.description: Enumerated status values for Order.

entries.name: schema:Organization
entries.description: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

entries.name: schema:OrganizationRole
entries.description: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.

entries.name: schema:OrganizeAction
entries.description: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.

entries.name: schema:OutletStore
entries.description: An outlet store.

entries.name: schema:OwnershipInfo
entries.description: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

entries.name: schema:PaintAction
entries.description: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

entries.name: schema:Painting
entries.description: A painting.

entries.name: schema:PalliativeProcedure
entries.description: A medical procedure intended primarily for palliative purposes, aimed at relieving the symptoms of an underlying health condition.

entries.name: schema:ParcelDelivery
entries.description: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.

entries.name: schema:ParentAudience
entries.description: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

entries.name: schema:Park
entries.description: A park.

entries.name: schema:ParkingFacility
entries.description: A parking lot or other parking facility.

entries.name: schema:PathologyTest
entries.description: A medical test performed by a laboratory that typically involves examination of a tissue sample by a pathologist.

entries.name: schema:Patient
entries.description: A patient is any person recipient of health care services.

entries.name: schema:PawnShop
entries.description: A shop that will buy, or lend money against the security of, personal possessions.

entries.name: schema:PayAction
entries.description: An agent pays a price to a participant.

entries.name: schema:PaymentCard
entries.description: A payment method using a credit, debit, store or other card to associate the payment with an account.

entries.name: schema:PaymentChargeSpecification
entries.description: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

entries.name: schema:PaymentMethod
entries.description:
A payment method is a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase. Payment methods are characterized by the legal and technical structures used, and by the organization or group carrying out the transaction. The following legacy values should be accepted: 

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByInvoice
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Cash
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#CheckInAdvance
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#COD
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DirectDebit
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#GoogleCheckout
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PayPal
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PaySwarm

Structured values, or [UNCE payment means](https://vocabulary.uncefact.org/PaymentMeans) are recommended or for newer annotations.

entries.name: schema:PaymentMethodType
entries.description: The type of payment method, only for generic payment types, specific forms of payments, like card payment should be expressed using subclasses of PaymentMethod.

entries.name: schema:PaymentService
entries.description: A Service to transfer funds from a person or organization to a beneficiary person or organization.

entries.name: schema:PaymentStatusType
entries.description: A specific payment status. For example, PaymentDue, PaymentComplete, etc.

entries.name: schema:PeopleAudience
entries.description: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

entries.name: schema:PerformAction
entries.description: The act of participating in performance arts.

entries.name: schema:PerformanceRole
entries.description: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

entries.name: schema:PerformingArtsEvent
entries.description:
Live performance Event of the performing arts (music, theatre, dance, acrobatics, spoken word), including performance art and performative sports (e.g. choreographed forms of martial arts, figure skating, competitive ballroom dancing).

Note: Use additionalType to differentiate between productions / shows (PerformanceWork, EventSeries), tours (EventSeries), and individual performances.

entries.name: schema:PerformingArtsTheater
entries.description: A theater or other performing art center.

entries.name: schema:PerformingGroup
entries.description: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

entries.name: schema:Periodical
entries.description: A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended to continue indefinitely, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

entries.name: schema:Permit
entries.description: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

entries.name: schema:Person
entries.description: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

entries.name: schema:PetStore
entries.description: A pet store.

entries.name: schema:Pharmacy
entries.description: A pharmacy or drugstore.

entries.name: schema:Photograph
entries.description: A photograph.

entries.name: schema:PhotographAction
entries.description: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

entries.name: schema:PhysicalActivity
entries.description: Any bodily activity that enhances or maintains physical fitness and overall health and wellness. Includes activity that is part of daily living and routine, structured exercise, and exercise prescribed as part of a medical treatment or recovery plan.

entries.name: schema:PhysicalActivityCategory
entries.description: Categories of physical activity, organized by physiologic classification.

entries.name: schema:PhysicalExam
entries.description: A type of physical examination of a patient performed by a physician.

entries.name: schema:PhysicalTherapy
entries.description: A process of progressive physical care and rehabilitation aimed at improving a health condition.

entries.name: schema:Physician
entries.description: An individual physician or a physician's office considered as a [[MedicalOrganization]].

entries.name: schema:PhysiciansOffice
entries.description: A doctor's office or clinic.

entries.name: schema:Place
entries.description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

entries.name: schema:PlaceOfWorship
entries.description: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

entries.name: schema:PlanAction
entries.description: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

entries.name: schema:Play
entries.description: A play is a form of literature, usually consisting of dialogue between characters, intended for theatrical performance rather than just reading. Note: A performance of a Play would be a [[TheaterEvent]] or [[BroadcastEvent]] - the *Play* being the [[workPerformed]].

entries.name: schema:PlayAction
entries.description:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, competition or exercise.

Related actions:

* [[ListenAction]]: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
* [[WatchAction]]: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.

entries.name: schema:PlayGameAction
entries.description: The act of playing a video game.

entries.name: schema:Playground
entries.description: A playground.

entries.name: schema:Plumber
entries.description: A plumbing service.

entries.name: schema:PodcastEpisode
entries.description: A single episode of a podcast series.

entries.name: schema:PodcastSeason
entries.description: A single season of a podcast. Many podcasts do not break down into separate seasons. In that case, PodcastSeries should be used.

entries.name: schema:PodcastSeries
entries.description: A podcast is an episodic series of digital audio or video files which a user can download and listen to.

entries.name: schema:PoliceStation
entries.description: A police station.

entries.name: schema:PoliticalParty
entries.description: Organization: Political Party.

entries.name: schema:Pond
entries.description: A pond.

entries.name: schema:PostOffice
entries.description: A post office.

entries.name: schema:PostalAddress
entries.description: The mailing address.

entries.name: schema:PostalCodeRangeSpecification
entries.description: Indicates a range of postal codes, usually defined as the set of valid codes between [[postalCodeBegin]] and [[postalCodeEnd]], inclusively.

entries.name: schema:Poster
entries.description: A large, usually printed placard, bill, or announcement, often illustrated, that is posted to advertise or publicize something.

entries.name: schema:PreOrderAction
entries.description: An agent orders a (not yet released) object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

entries.name: schema:PrependAction
entries.description: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

entries.name: schema:Preschool
entries.description: A preschool.

entries.name: schema:PresentationDigitalDocument
entries.description: A file containing slides or used for a presentation.

entries.name: schema:PreventionIndication
entries.description: An indication for preventing an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

entries.name: schema:PriceComponentTypeEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates different price components that together make up the total price for an offered product.

entries.name: schema:PriceSpecification
entries.description: A structured value representing a price or price range. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup. It is recommended to use [[MonetaryAmount]] to describe independent amounts of money such as a salary, credit card limits, etc.

entries.name: schema:PriceTypeEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates different price types, for example list price, invoice price, and sale price.

entries.name: schema:Product
entries.description: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

entries.name: schema:ProductCollection
entries.description: A set of products (either [[ProductGroup]]s or specific variants) that are listed together e.g. in an [[Offer]].

entries.name: schema:ProductGroup
entries.description:
A ProductGroup represents a group of [[Product]]s that vary only in certain well-described ways, such as by [[size]], [[color]], [[material]] etc.

While a ProductGroup itself is not directly offered for sale, the various varying products that it represents can be. The ProductGroup serves as a prototype or template, standing in for all of the products who have an [[isVariantOf]] relationship to it. As such, properties (including additional types) can be applied to the ProductGroup to represent characteristics shared by each of the (possibly very many) variants. Properties that reference a ProductGroup are not included in this mechanism; neither are the following specific properties [[variesBy]], [[hasVariant]], [[url]].

entries.name: schema:ProductModel
entries.description: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

entries.name: schema:ProfessionalService
entries.description:
Original definition: "provider of professional services."\n\nThe general [[ProfessionalService]] type for local businesses was deprecated due to confusion with [[Service]]. For reference, the types that it included were: [[Dentist]],
        [[AccountingService]], [[Attorney]], [[Notary]], as well as types for several kinds of [[HomeAndConstructionBusiness]]: [[Electrician]], [[GeneralContractor]],
        [[HousePainter]], [[Locksmith]], [[Plumber]], [[RoofingContractor]]. [[LegalService]] was introduced as a more inclusive supertype of [[Attorney]].

entries.name: schema:ProfilePage
entries.description: Web page type: Profile page.

entries.name: schema:ProgramMembership
entries.description: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.

entries.name: schema:Project
entries.description:
An enterprise (potentially individual but typically collaborative), planned to achieve a particular aim.
Use properties from [[Organization]], [[subOrganization]]/[[parentOrganization]] to indicate project sub-structures.

entries.name: schema:PronounceableText
entries.description: Data type: PronounceableText.

entries.name: schema:Property
entries.description: A property, used to indicate attributes and relationships of some Thing; equivalent to rdf:Property.

entries.name: schema:PropertyValue
entries.description: A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.\n\n Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.

entries.name: schema:PropertyValueSpecification
entries.description: A Property value specification.

entries.name: schema:Protein
entries.description: Protein is here used in its widest possible definition, as classes of amino acid based molecules. Amyloid-beta Protein in human (UniProt P05067), eukaryota (e.g. an OrthoDB group) or even a single molecule that one can point to are all of type :Protein. A protein can thus be a subclass of another protein, e.g. :Protein as a UniProt record can have multiple isoforms inside it which would also be :Protein. They can be imagined, synthetic, hypothetical or naturally occurring.

entries.name: schema:PsychologicalTreatment
entries.description: A process of care relying upon counseling, dialogue and communication  aimed at improving a mental health condition without use of drugs.

entries.name: schema:PublicSwimmingPool
entries.description: A public swimming pool.

entries.name: schema:PublicToilet
entries.description: A public toilet is a room or small building containing one or more toilets (and possibly also urinals) which is available for use by the general public, or by customers or employees of certain businesses.

entries.name: schema:PublicationEvent
entries.description: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type, e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

entries.name: schema:PublicationIssue
entries.description: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

entries.name: schema:PublicationVolume
entries.description: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

entries.name: schema:PurchaseType
entries.description: Enumerates a purchase type for an item.

entries.name: schema:QAPage
entries.description: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

entries.name: schema:QualitativeValue
entries.description: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.

entries.name: schema:QuantitativeValue
entries.description: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

entries.name: schema:QuantitativeValueDistribution
entries.description: A statistical distribution of values.

entries.name: schema:Quantity
entries.description: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 kg' or '4 milligrams'.

entries.name: schema:Question
entries.description: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

entries.name: schema:Quiz
entries.description: Quiz: A test of knowledge, skills and abilities.

entries.name: schema:Quotation
entries.description: A quotation. Often but not necessarily from some written work, attributable to a real world author and - if associated with a fictional character - to any fictional Person. Use [[isBasedOn]] to link to source/origin. The [[recordedIn]] property can be used to reference a Quotation from an [[Event]].

entries.name: schema:QuoteAction
entries.description: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

entries.name: schema:RVPark
entries.description: A place offering space for "Recreational Vehicles", Caravans, mobile homes and the like.

entries.name: schema:RadiationTherapy
entries.description: A process of care using radiation aimed at improving a health condition.

entries.name: schema:RadioBroadcastService
entries.description: A delivery service through which radio content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

entries.name: schema:RadioChannel
entries.description: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

entries.name: schema:RadioClip
entries.description: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

entries.name: schema:RadioEpisode
entries.description: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

entries.name: schema:RadioSeason
entries.description: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

entries.name: schema:RadioSeries
entries.description: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

entries.name: schema:RadioStation
entries.description: A radio station.

entries.name: schema:Rating
entries.description: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

entries.name: schema:ReactAction
entries.description: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

entries.name: schema:ReadAction
entries.description: The act of consuming written content.

entries.name: schema:RealEstateAgent
entries.description: A real-estate agent.

entries.name: schema:RealEstateListing
entries.description:
A [[RealEstateListing]] is a listing that describes one or more real-estate [[Offer]]s (whose [[businessFunction]] is typically to lease out, or to sell).
  The [[RealEstateListing]] type itself represents the overall listing, as manifested in some [[WebPage]].

entries.name: schema:ReceiveAction
entries.description:
The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object that has been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.

Related actions:

* [[SendAction]]: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.
* [[TakeAction]]: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transferred (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine).

entries.name: schema:Recipe
entries.description: A recipe. For dietary restrictions covered by the recipe, a few common restrictions are enumerated via [[suitableForDiet]]. The [[keywords]] property can also be used to add more detail.

entries.name: schema:Recommendation
entries.description: [[Recommendation]] is a type of [[Review]] that suggests or proposes something as the best option or best course of action. Recommendations may be for products or services, or other concrete things, as in the case of a ranked list or product guide. A [[Guide]] may list multiple recommendations for different categories. For example, in a [[Guide]] about which TVs to buy, the author may have several [[Recommendation]]s.

entries.name: schema:RecommendedDoseSchedule
entries.description: A recommended dosing schedule for a drug or supplement as prescribed or recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

entries.name: schema:RecyclingCenter
entries.description: A recycling center.

entries.name: schema:RefundTypeEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates several kinds of product return refund types.

entries.name: schema:RegisterAction
entries.description:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

entries.name: schema:RejectAction
entries.description:
The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

* [[AcceptAction]]: The antonym of RejectAction.

entries.name: schema:RentAction
entries.description: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

entries.name: schema:RentalCarReservation
entries.description: A reservation for a rental car.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

entries.name: schema:RepaymentSpecification
entries.description: A structured value representing repayment.

entries.name: schema:ReplaceAction
entries.description: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

entries.name: schema:ReplyAction
entries.description:
The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to [[AskAction]].

Related actions:

* [[AskAction]]: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction.

entries.name: schema:Report
entries.description: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

entries.name: schema:ReportageNewsArticle
entries.description:
The [[ReportageNewsArticle]] type is a subtype of [[NewsArticle]] representing
 news articles which are the result of journalistic news reporting conventions.

In practice many news publishers produce a wide variety of article types, many of which might be considered a [[NewsArticle]] but not a [[ReportageNewsArticle]]. For example, opinion pieces, reviews, analysis, sponsored or satirical articles, or articles that combine several of these elements.

The [[ReportageNewsArticle]] type is based on a stricter ideal for "news" as a work of journalism, with articles based on factual information either observed or verified by the author, or reported and verified from knowledgeable sources.  This often includes perspectives from multiple viewpoints on a particular issue (distinguishing news reports from public relations or propaganda).  News reports in the [[ReportageNewsArticle]] sense de-emphasize the opinion of the author, with commentary and value judgements typically expressed elsewhere.

A [[ReportageNewsArticle]] which goes deeper into analysis can also be marked with an additional type of [[AnalysisNewsArticle]].

entries.name: schema:ReportedDoseSchedule
entries.description: A patient-reported or observed dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

entries.name: schema:ResearchOrganization
entries.description: A Research Organization (e.g. scientific institute, research company).

entries.name: schema:ResearchProject
entries.description: A Research project.

entries.name: schema:Researcher
entries.description: Researchers.

entries.name: schema:Reservation
entries.description: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use [[Offer]].

entries.name: schema:ReservationPackage
entries.description: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

entries.name: schema:ReservationStatusType
entries.description: Enumerated status values for Reservation.

entries.name: schema:ReserveAction
entries.description:
Reserving a concrete object.

Related actions:

* [[ScheduleAction]]: Unlike ScheduleAction, ReserveAction reserves concrete objects (e.g. a table, a hotel) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

entries.name: schema:Reservoir
entries.description: A reservoir of water, typically an artificially created lake, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

entries.name: schema:ResetPasswordAction
entries.description: The action of resetting the password of a device or application.

entries.name: schema:Residence
entries.description: The place where a person lives.

entries.name: schema:Resort
entries.description:
A resort is a place used for relaxation or recreation, attracting visitors for holidays or vacations. Resorts are places, towns or sometimes commercial establishments operated by a single company (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

entries.name: schema:Restaurant
entries.description: A restaurant.

entries.name: schema:RestrictedDiet
entries.description: A diet restricted to certain foods or preparations for cultural, religious, health or lifestyle reasons.

entries.name: schema:ResumeAction
entries.description: The act of resuming a device or application which was formerly paused (e.g. resume music playback or resume a timer).

entries.name: schema:ReturnAction
entries.description: The act of returning to the origin that which was previously received (concrete objects) or taken (ownership).

entries.name: schema:ReturnFeesEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates several kinds of policies for product return fees.

entries.name: schema:ReturnLabelSourceEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates several types of return labels for product returns.

entries.name: schema:ReturnMethodEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates several types of product return methods.

entries.name: schema:Review
entries.description: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

entries.name: schema:ReviewAction
entries.description: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

entries.name: schema:ReviewNewsArticle
entries.description: A [[NewsArticle]] and [[CriticReview]] providing a professional critic's assessment of a service, product, performance, or artistic or literary work.

entries.name: schema:RiverBodyOfWater
entries.description: A river (for example, the broad majestic Shannon).

entries.name: schema:Role
entries.description: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/06/16/introducing-role/).

entries.name: schema:RoofingContractor
entries.description: A roofing contractor.

entries.name: schema:Room
entries.description:
A room is a distinguishable space within a structure, usually separated from other spaces by interior walls (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

entries.name: schema:RsvpAction
entries.description: The act of notifying an event organizer as to whether you expect to attend the event.

entries.name: schema:RsvpResponseType
entries.description: RsvpResponseType is an enumeration type whose instances represent responding to an RSVP request.

entries.name: schema:RuntimePlatform
entries.description: Specialized software environment that provides the essential infrastructure, libraries, and services required to execute a program.

entries.name: schema:SaleEvent
entries.description: Event type: Sales event.

entries.name: schema:SatiricalArticle
entries.description: An [[Article]] whose content is primarily [[satirical]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satire) in nature, i.e. unlikely to be literally true. A satirical article is sometimes but not necessarily also a [[NewsArticle]]. [[ScholarlyArticle]]s are also sometimes satirized.

entries.name: schema:Schedule
entries.description:
A schedule defines a repeating time period used to describe a regularly occurring [[Event]]. At a minimum a schedule will specify [[repeatFrequency]] which describes the interval between occurrences of the event. Additional information can be provided to specify the schedule more precisely.
      This includes identifying the day(s) of the week or month when the recurring event will take place, in addition to its start and end time. Schedules may also
      have start and end dates to indicate when they are active, e.g. to define a limited calendar of events.

entries.name: schema:ScheduleAction
entries.description:
Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.

Related actions:

* [[ReserveAction]]: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

entries.name: schema:ScholarlyArticle
entries.description: A scholarly article.

entries.name: schema:School
entries.description: A school.

entries.name: schema:SchoolDistrict
entries.description: A School District is an administrative area for the administration of schools.

entries.name: schema:ScreeningEvent
entries.description: A screening of a movie or other video.

entries.name: schema:Sculpture
entries.description: A piece of sculpture.

entries.name: schema:SeaBodyOfWater
entries.description: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

entries.name: schema:SearchAction
entries.description:
The act of searching for an object.

Related actions:

* [[FindAction]]: SearchAction generally leads to a FindAction, but not necessarily.

entries.name: schema:SearchRescueOrganization
entries.description: A Search and Rescue organization of some kind.

entries.name: schema:SearchResultsPage
entries.description: Web page type: Search results page.

entries.name: schema:Season
entries.description: A media season, e.g. TV, radio, video game etc.

entries.name: schema:Seat
entries.description: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

entries.name: schema:SeekToAction
entries.description: This is the [[Action]] of navigating to a specific [[startOffset]] timestamp within a [[VideoObject]], typically represented with a URL template structure.

entries.name: schema:SelfStorage
entries.description: A self-storage facility.

entries.name: schema:SellAction
entries.description: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

entries.name: schema:SendAction
entries.description:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination. Related actions:

* [[ReceiveAction]]: The reciprocal of SendAction.
* [[GiveAction]]: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

entries.name: schema:SequentialArt
entries.description: An art forms that use images deployed in a specific order for the purpose of graphic storytelling (i.e., narration of graphic stories) or conveying information. Examples of SequentialArt are Franco-Belgian Bande Dessine, Comics in the USA and  (Manga) in Japan.

entries.name: schema:Series
entries.description: A Series in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. See also [[CreativeWorkSeries]], [[EventSeries]].

entries.name: schema:Service
entries.description: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

entries.name: schema:ServiceChannel
entries.description: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

entries.name: schema:ServicePeriod
entries.description: ServicePeriod represents a duration with some constraints about cutoff time and business days. This is used e.g. in shipping for handling times or transit time.

entries.name: schema:ShareAction
entries.description: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

entries.name: schema:SheetMusic
entries.description: Printed music, as opposed to performed or recorded music.

entries.name: schema:ShippingConditions
entries.description: ShippingConditions represent a set of constraints and information about the conditions of shipping a product. Such conditions may apply to only a subset of the products being shipped, depending on aspects of the product like weight, size, price, destination, and others. All the specified conditions must be met for this ShippingConditions to apply.

entries.name: schema:ShippingDeliveryTime
entries.description: ShippingDeliveryTime provides various pieces of information about delivery times for shipping.

entries.name: schema:ShippingRateSettings
entries.description: A ShippingRateSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the [[shippingSettingsLink]] property of an [[OfferShippingDetails]]. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished and matched (i.e. identified/referenced) by their different values for [[shippingLabel]].

entries.name: schema:ShippingService
entries.description: ShippingService represents the criteria used to determine if and how an offer could be shipped to a customer.

entries.name: schema:ShoeStore
entries.description: A shoe store.

entries.name: schema:ShoppingCenter
entries.description: A shopping center or mall.

entries.name: schema:ShortStory
entries.description: Short story or tale. A brief work of literature, usually written in narrative prose.

entries.name: schema:SingleFamilyResidence
entries.description: Residence type: Single-family home.

entries.name: schema:SiteNavigationElement
entries.description: A navigation element of the page.

entries.name: schema:SizeGroupEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates common size groups for various product categories.

entries.name: schema:SizeSpecification
entries.description: Size related properties of a product, typically a size code ([[name]]) and optionally a [[sizeSystem]], [[sizeGroup]], and product measurements ([[hasMeasurement]]). In addition, the intended audience can be defined through [[suggestedAge]], [[suggestedGender]], and suggested body measurements ([[suggestedMeasurement]]).

entries.name: schema:SizeSystemEnumeration
entries.description: Enumerates common size systems for different categories of products, for example "EN-13402" or "UK" for wearables or "Imperial" for screws.

entries.name: schema:SkiResort
entries.description: A ski resort.

entries.name: schema:SocialEvent
entries.description: Event type: Social event.

entries.name: schema:SocialMediaPosting
entries.description: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

entries.name: schema:SoftwareApplication
entries.description: A software application.

entries.name: schema:SoftwareSourceCode
entries.description: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

entries.name: schema:SolveMathAction
entries.description: The action that takes in a math expression and directs users to a page potentially capable of solving/simplifying that expression.

entries.name: schema:SomeProducts
entries.description: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

entries.name: schema:SpeakableSpecification
entries.description: A SpeakableSpecification indicates (typically via [[xpath]] or [[cssSelector]]) sections of a document that are highlighted as particularly [[speakable]]. Instances of this type are expected to be used primarily as values of the [[speakable]] property.

entries.name: schema:SpecialAnnouncement
entries.description:
A SpecialAnnouncement combines a simple date-stamped textual information update
      with contextualized Web links and other structured data.  It represents an information update made by a
      locally-oriented organization, for example schools, pharmacies, healthcare providers,  community groups, police,
      local government.

For work in progress guidelines on Coronavirus-related markup see [this doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/14ikaGCKxo50rRM7nvKSlbUpjyIk2WMQd3IkB1lItlrM/edit#).

The motivating scenario for SpecialAnnouncement is the [Coronavirus pandemic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_pandemic), and the initial vocabulary is oriented to this urgent situation. Schema.org
expect to improve the markup iteratively as it is deployed and as feedback emerges from use. In addition to our
usual [Github entry](https://github.com/schemaorg/schemaorg/issues/2490), feedback comments can also be provided in [this document](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fpdFFxk8s87CWwACs53SGkYv3aafSxz_DTtOQxMrBJQ/edit#).


While this schema is designed to communicate urgent crisis-related information, it is not the same as an emergency warning technology like [CAP](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_Alerting_Protocol), although there may be overlaps. The intent is to cover
the kinds of everyday practical information being posted to existing websites during an emergency situation.

Several kinds of information can be provided:

We encourage the provision of "name", "text", "datePosted", "expires" (if appropriate), "category" and
"url" as a simple baseline. It is important to provide a value for "category" where possible, most ideally as a well known
URL from Wikipedia or Wikidata. In the case of the 2019-2020 Coronavirus pandemic, this should be "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2019-20\_coronavirus\_pandemic" or "https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q81068910".

For many of the possible properties, values can either be simple links or an inline description, depending on whether a summary is available. For a link, provide just the URL of the appropriate page as the property's value. For an inline description, use a [[WebContent]] type, and provide the url as a property of that, alongside at least a simple "[[text]]" summary of the page. It is
unlikely that a single SpecialAnnouncement will need all of the possible properties simultaneously.

We expect that in many cases the page referenced might contain more specialized structured data, e.g. contact info, [[openingHours]], [[Event]], [[FAQPage]] etc. By linking to those pages from a [[SpecialAnnouncement]] you can help make it clearer that the events are related to the situation (e.g. Coronavirus) indicated by the [[category]] property of the [[SpecialAnnouncement]].

Many [[SpecialAnnouncement]]s will relate to particular regions and to identifiable local organizations. Use [[spatialCoverage]] for the region, and [[announcementLocation]] to indicate specific [[LocalBusiness]]es and [[CivicStructure]]s. If the announcement affects both a particular region and a specific location (for example, a library closure that serves an entire region), use both [[spatialCoverage]] and [[announcementLocation]].

The [[about]] property can be used to indicate entities that are the focus of the announcement. We now recommend using [[about]] only
for representing non-location entities (e.g. a [[Course]] or a [[RadioStation]]). For places, use [[announcementLocation]] and [[spatialCoverage]]. Consumers of this markup should be aware that the initial design encouraged the use of [[about]] for locations too.

The basic content of [[SpecialAnnouncement]] is similar to that of an [RSS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSS) or [Atom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atom_(Web_standard)) feed. For publishers without such feeds, basic feed-like information can be shared by posting
[[SpecialAnnouncement]] updates in a page, e.g. using JSON-LD. For sites with Atom/RSS functionality, you can point to a feed
with the [[webFeed]] property. This can be a simple URL, or an inline [[DataFeed]] object, with [[encodingFormat]] providing
media type information, e.g. "application/rss+xml" or "application/atom+xml".

entries.name: schema:Specialty
