entries.name: schema:coursePrerequisites
entries.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

entries.name: schema:courseSchedule
entries.description: Represents the length and pace of a course, expressed as a [[Schedule]].

entries.name: schema:courseWorkload
entries.description: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

entries.name: schema:coverageEndTime
entries.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

entries.name: schema:coverageStartTime
entries.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

entries.name: schema:creativeWorkStatus
entries.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

entries.name: schema:creator
entries.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:credentialCategory
entries.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree, certificate, badge, or more specific term.

entries.name: schema:creditText
entries.description: Text that can be used to credit person(s) and/or organization(s) associated with a published Creative Work.

entries.name: schema:creditedTo
entries.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

entries.name: schema:cssSelector
entries.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

entries.name: schema:currenciesAccepted
entries.description: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

entries.name: schema:currency
entries.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

entries.name: schema:currentExchangeRate
entries.description: The current price of a currency.

entries.name: schema:customer
entries.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

entries.name: schema:customerRemorseReturnFees
entries.description: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

entries.name: schema:customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
entries.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

entries.name: schema:customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
entries.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

entries.name: schema:cutoffTime
entries.description: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

entries.name: schema:cvdCollectionDate
entries.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

entries.name: schema:cvdFacilityCounty
entries.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

entries.name: schema:cvdFacilityId
entries.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumBeds
entries.description: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumBedsOcc
entries.description: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumC19Died
entries.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumC19HOPats
entries.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumC19HospPats
entries.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumC19MechVentPats
entries.description: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
entries.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumC19OverflowPats
entries.description: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumICUBeds
entries.description: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumICUBedsOcc
entries.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumTotBeds
entries.description: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumVent
entries.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

entries.name: schema:cvdNumVentUse
entries.description: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

entries.name: schema:data
entries.description: Data associated with the event, like for instance a log message.

entries.name: schema:dataFeedElement
entries.description: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

entries.name: schema:dataset
entries.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

entries.name: schema:datasetTimeInterval
entries.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

entries.name: schema:dateCreated
entries.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

entries.name: schema:dateDeleted
entries.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

entries.name: schema:dateIssued
entries.description: The date the ticket was issued.

entries.name: schema:dateModified
entries.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

entries.name: schema:datePosted
entries.description: Publication date of an online listing.

entries.name: schema:datePublished
entries.description: Date of first publication or broadcast. For example the date a [[CreativeWork]] was broadcast or a [[Certification]] was issued.

entries.name: schema:dateRead
entries.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

entries.name: schema:dateReceived
entries.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

entries.name: schema:dateSent
entries.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

entries.name: schema:dateVehicleFirstRegistered
entries.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

entries.name: schema:dateline
entries.description:
A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.

Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created, e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, use [[contentLocation]].

Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

entries.name: schema:dayOfWeek
entries.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

entries.name: schema:deathDate
entries.description: Date of death.

entries.name: schema:deathPlace
entries.description: The place where the person died.

entries.name: schema:defaultValue
entries.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

entries.name: schema:deliveryAddress
entries.description: Destination address.

entries.name: schema:deliveryLeadTime
entries.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

entries.name: schema:deliveryMethod
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

entries.name: schema:deliveryStatus
entries.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

entries.name: schema:deliveryTime
entries.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

entries.name: schema:department
entries.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

entries.name: schema:departureAirport
entries.description: The airport where the flight originates.

entries.name: schema:departureBoatTerminal
entries.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

entries.name: schema:departureBusStop
entries.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

entries.name: schema:departureGate
entries.description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

entries.name: schema:departurePlatform
entries.description: The platform from which the train departs.

entries.name: schema:departureStation
entries.description: The station from which the train departs.

entries.name: schema:departureTerminal
entries.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

entries.name: schema:departureTime
entries.description: The expected departure time.

entries.name: schema:dependencies
entries.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

entries.name: schema:depth
entries.description: The depth of the item.

entries.name: schema:description
entries.description: A description of the item.

entries.name: schema:device
entries.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

entries.name: schema:diagnosis
entries.description: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

entries.name: schema:diagram
entries.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

entries.name: schema:diet
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

entries.name: schema:dietFeatures
entries.description: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

entries.name: schema:differentialDiagnosis
entries.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

entries.name: schema:digitalSourceType
entries.description: Indicates an IPTCDigitalSourceEnumeration code indicating the nature of the digital source(s) for some [[CreativeWork]].

entries.name: schema:directApply
entries.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

entries.name: schema:director
entries.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

entries.name: schema:directors
entries.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

entries.name: schema:disambiguatingDescription
entries.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

entries.name: schema:discount
entries.description: Any discount applied (to an Order).

entries.name: schema:discountCode
entries.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

entries.name: schema:discountCurrency
entries.description: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

entries.name: schema:discusses
entries.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

entries.name: schema:discussionUrl
entries.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:diseasePreventionInfo
entries.description: Information about disease prevention.

entries.name: schema:diseaseSpreadStatistics
entries.description:
Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as [[WebContent]], or
  described directly as a [[Dataset]], or the specific [[Observation]]s in the dataset. When a [[WebContent]] URL is
  provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

entries.name: schema:displayLocation
entries.description: The location at which an item can be viewed or experienced in-person.

entries.name: schema:dissolutionDate
entries.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

entries.name: schema:distance
entries.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

entries.name: schema:distinguishingSign
entries.description: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

entries.name: schema:distribution
entries.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

entries.name: schema:diversityPolicy
entries.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsrooms diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

entries.name: schema:diversityStaffingReport
entries.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

entries.name: schema:documentation
entries.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

entries.name: schema:doesNotShip
entries.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

entries.name: schema:domainIncludes
entries.description: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

entries.name: schema:domiciledMortgage
entries.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

entries.name: schema:doorTime
entries.description: The time admission will commence.

entries.name: schema:dosageForm
entries.description: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

entries.name: schema:doseSchedule
entries.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

entries.name: schema:doseUnit
entries.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

entries.name: schema:doseValue
entries.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

entries.name: schema:downPayment
entries.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

entries.name: schema:downloadUrl
entries.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

entries.name: schema:downvoteCount
entries.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

entries.name: schema:drainsTo
entries.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

entries.name: schema:driveWheelConfiguration
entries.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

entries.name: schema:dropoffLocation
entries.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

entries.name: schema:dropoffTime
entries.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

entries.name: schema:drug
entries.description: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

entries.name: schema:drugClass
entries.description: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

entries.name: schema:drugUnit
entries.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

entries.name: schema:duns
entries.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

entries.name: schema:duplicateTherapy
entries.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

entries.name: schema:duration
entries.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

entries.name: schema:durationOfWarranty
entries.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

entries.name: schema:duringMedia
entries.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

entries.name: schema:earlyPrepaymentPenalty
entries.description: The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

entries.name: schema:editEIDR
entries.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J" has several edits, e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

entries.name: schema:editor
entries.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:eduQuestionType
entries.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

entries.name: schema:educationRequirements
entries.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

entries.name: schema:educationalAlignment
entries.description:
An alignment to an established educational framework.

This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

entries.name: schema:educationalCredentialAwarded
entries.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

entries.name: schema:educationalFramework
entries.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

entries.name: schema:educationalLevel
entries.description: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

entries.name: schema:educationalProgramMode
entries.description: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

entries.name: schema:educationalRole
entries.description: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.

entries.name: schema:educationalUse
entries.description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

entries.name: schema:elevation
entries.description: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\_OF\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

entries.name: schema:eligibilityToWorkRequirement
entries.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

entries.name: schema:eligibleCustomerType
entries.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

entries.name: schema:eligibleDuration
entries.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

entries.name: schema:eligibleQuantity
entries.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

entries.name: schema:eligibleRegion
entries.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

entries.name: schema:eligibleTransactionVolume
entries.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

entries.name: schema:eligibleWithSupplier
entries.description: The supplier of the incentivized item/service for which the incentive is valid for such as a utility company, merchant, or contractor.

entries.name: schema:email
entries.description: Email address.

entries.name: schema:embedUrl
entries.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

entries.name: schema:embeddedTextCaption
entries.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

entries.name: schema:emissionsCO2
entries.description: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

entries.name: schema:employee
entries.description: Someone working for this organization.

entries.name: schema:employees
entries.description: People working for this organization.

entries.name: schema:employerOverview
entries.description: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

entries.name: schema:employmentType
entries.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

entries.name: schema:employmentUnit
entries.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

entries.name: schema:encodesBioChemEntity
entries.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

entries.name: schema:encodesCreativeWork
entries.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

entries.name: schema:encoding
entries.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

entries.name: schema:encodingFormat
entries.description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.

In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

entries.name: schema:encodingType
entries.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

entries.name: schema:encodings
entries.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:endDate
entries.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

entries.name: schema:endOffset
entries.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

entries.name: schema:endTime
entries.description: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

entries.name: schema:endorsee
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

entries.name: schema:endorsers
entries.description: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

entries.name: schema:energyEfficiencyScaleMax
entries.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

entries.name: schema:energyEfficiencyScaleMin
entries.description: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

entries.name: schema:engineDisplacement
entries.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:enginePower
entries.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine.
    Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see  [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine\_power\_test\_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 3: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:engineType
entries.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

entries.name: schema:entertainmentBusiness
entries.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

entries.name: schema:epidemiology
entries.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

entries.name: schema:episode
entries.description: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

entries.name: schema:episodeNumber
entries.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

entries.name: schema:episodes
entries.description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

entries.name: schema:equal
entries.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

entries.name: schema:error
entries.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure. Consider using the Error type.

entries.name: schema:errorCode
entries.description: Application or platform dependant error code.

entries.name: schema:estimatedCost
entries.description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

entries.name: schema:estimatedFlightDuration
entries.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

entries.name: schema:estimatedSalary
entries.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

entries.name: schema:estimatesRiskOf
entries.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

entries.name: schema:ethicsPolicy
entries.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

entries.name: schema:event
entries.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

entries.name: schema:eventAttendanceMode
entries.description: The eventAttendanceMode of an event indicates whether it occurs online, offline, or a mix.

entries.name: schema:eventSchedule
entries.description:
Associates an [[Event]] with a [[Schedule]]. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of
      repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly
      gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An [[Event]] that
      is associated with a [[Schedule]] using this property should not have [[startDate]] or [[endDate]] properties. These are instead defined within the associated
      [[Schedule]], this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The property might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months
      or seasons.

entries.name: schema:eventStatus
entries.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

entries.name: schema:events
entries.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

entries.name: schema:evidenceLevel
entries.description: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

entries.name: schema:evidenceOrigin
entries.description: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

entries.name: schema:exampleOfWork
entries.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

entries.name: schema:exceptDate
entries.description:
Defines a [[Date]] or [[DateTime]] during which a scheduled [[Event]] will not take place. The property allows exceptions to
      a [[Schedule]] to be specified. If an exception is specified as a [[DateTime]] then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time
      should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a [[Date]] then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be
      excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to be excluded from the schedule without having to itemise every scheduled event.

entries.name: schema:exchangeRateSpread
entries.description: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

entries.name: schema:executableLibraryName
entries.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

entries.name: schema:exerciseCourse
entries.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

entries.name: schema:exercisePlan
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

entries.name: schema:exerciseRelatedDiet
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

entries.name: schema:exerciseType
entries.description: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

entries.name: schema:exifData
entries.description: exif data for this object.

entries.name: schema:expectedArrivalFrom
entries.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

entries.name: schema:expectedArrivalUntil
entries.description: The latest date the package may arrive.

entries.name: schema:expectedPrognosis
entries.description: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

entries.name: schema:expectsAcceptanceOf
entries.description: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

entries.name: schema:experienceInPlaceOfEducation
entries.description: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

entries.name: schema:experienceRequirements
entries.description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

entries.name: schema:expertConsiderations
entries.description: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

entries.name: schema:expires
entries.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date, or a [[Certification]] the validity has expired.

entries.name: schema:expressedIn
entries.description: Tissue, organ, biological sample, etc in which activity of this gene has been observed experimentally. For example brain, digestive system.

entries.name: schema:extendedAddress
entries.description: An address extension such as an apartment number, C/O or alternative name.

entries.name: schema:familyName
entries.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

entries.name: schema:fatContent
entries.description: The number of grams of fat.

entries.name: schema:faxNumber
entries.description: The fax number.

entries.name: schema:featureList
entries.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

entries.name: schema:feesAndCommissionsSpecification
entries.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

entries.name: schema:fiberContent
entries.description: The number of grams of fiber.

entries.name: schema:fileFormat
entries.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)) of the content, e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

entries.name: schema:fileSize
entries.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

entries.name: schema:financialAidEligible
entries.description: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

entries.name: schema:firstAppearance
entries.description: Indicates the first known occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

entries.name: schema:firstPerformance
entries.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

entries.name: schema:flightDistance
entries.description: The distance of the flight.

entries.name: schema:flightNumber
entries.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

entries.name: schema:floorLevel
entries.description:
The floor level for an [[Accommodation]] in a multi-storey building. Since counting
  systems [vary internationally](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey#Consecutive_number_floor_designations), the local system should be used where possible.

entries.name: schema:floorLimit
entries.description: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

entries.name: schema:floorSize
entries.description:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard.

entries.name: schema:followee
entries.description: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

entries.name: schema:follows
entries.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

entries.name: schema:followup
entries.description: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

entries.name: schema:foodEstablishment
entries.description: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

entries.name: schema:foodEvent
entries.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

entries.name: schema:foodWarning
entries.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

entries.name: schema:founder
entries.description: A person or organization who founded this organization.

entries.name: schema:founders
entries.description: A person who founded this organization.

entries.name: schema:foundingDate
entries.description: The date that this organization was founded.

entries.name: schema:foundingLocation
entries.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

entries.name: schema:free
entries.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

entries.name: schema:freeShippingThreshold
entries.description: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

entries.name: schema:frequency
entries.description: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

entries.name: schema:fromLocation
entries.description: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

entries.name: schema:fuelCapacity
entries.description: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

entries.name: schema:fuelConsumption
entries.description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

entries.name: schema:fuelEfficiency
entries.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

entries.name: schema:fuelType
entries.description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

entries.name: schema:fulfillmentType
entries.description: Type of fulfillment applicable to the [[ShippingService]].

entries.name: schema:functionalClass
entries.description: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

entries.name: schema:fundedItem
entries.description: Indicates something directly or indirectly funded or sponsored through a [[Grant]]. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

entries.name: schema:funder
entries.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

entries.name: schema:funding
entries.description: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

entries.name: schema:game
entries.description: Video game which is played on this server.

entries.name: schema:gameAvailabilityType
entries.description: Indicates the availability type of the game content associated with this action, such as whether it is a full version or a demo.

entries.name: schema:gameEdition
entries.description: The edition of a video game.

entries.name: schema:gameItem
entries.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

entries.name: schema:gameLocation
entries.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

entries.name: schema:gamePlatform
entries.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

entries.name: schema:gameServer
entries.description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

entries.name: schema:gameTip
entries.description: Links to tips, tactics, etc.

entries.name: schema:gender
entries.description: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who are not a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

entries.name: schema:genre
entries.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

entries.name: schema:geo
entries.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

entries.name: schema:geoContains
entries.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geoCoveredBy
entries.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geoCovers
entries.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geoCrosses
entries.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geoDisjoint
entries.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

entries.name: schema:geoEquals
entries.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).

entries.name: schema:geoIntersects
entries.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geoMidpoint
entries.description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

entries.name: schema:geoOverlaps
entries.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geoRadius
entries.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

entries.name: schema:geoTouches
entries.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

entries.name: schema:geoWithin
entries.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

entries.name: schema:geographicArea
entries.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

entries.name: schema:gettingTestedInfo
entries.description: Information about getting tested (for a [[MedicalCondition]]), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

entries.name: schema:givenName
entries.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

entries.name: schema:globalLocationNumber
entries.description: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

entries.name: schema:governmentBenefitsInfo
entries.description: governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

entries.name: schema:gracePeriod
entries.description: The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.

entries.name: schema:grantee
entries.description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

entries.name: schema:greater
entries.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

entries.name: schema:greaterOrEqual
entries.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

entries.name: schema:gtin
entries.description:
A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes.

A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties.

The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) expresses GTINs as URLs (URIs, IRIs, etc.).
Digital Links should be populated into the [[hasGS1DigitalLink]] attribute.

Note also that this is a definition for how to include GTINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of GTINs in general - see the GS1 documentation for authoritative details.

entries.name: schema:gtin12
entries.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

entries.name: schema:gtin13
entries.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

entries.name: schema:gtin14
entries.description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

entries.name: schema:gtin8
entries.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

entries.name: schema:guideline
entries.description: A medical guideline related to this entity.

entries.name: schema:guidelineDate
entries.description: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

entries.name: schema:guidelineSubject
entries.description: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

entries.name: schema:handlingTime
entries.description:
The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

In the context of [[ShippingDeliveryTime]], Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).  This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates.

In the context of [[ShippingService]], use the [[ServicePeriod]] format, that contains the same information in a structured form, with cut-off time, business days and duration.

entries.name: schema:hasAdultConsideration
entries.description: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

entries.name: schema:hasBioChemEntityPart
entries.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.

entries.name: schema:hasBioPolymerSequence
entries.description: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEntity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

entries.name: schema:hasBroadcastChannel
entries.description: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

entries.name: schema:hasCategoryCode
entries.description: A Category code contained in this code set.

entries.name: schema:hasCertification
entries.description: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

No information is implied about whether the course is mandatory or optional; no guarantee is implied about whether the course will be available to everyone on the program.

entries.name: schema:hasDigitalDocumentPermission

entries.name: schema:hasDriveThroughService

In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

entries.name: schema:hasEnergyConsumptionDetails

entries.name: schema:hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory
entries.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

entries.name: schema:hasGS1DigitalLink
entries.description:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be present on instances of [[IndividualProduct]]
  • A Digital Link that contains a lot number (AI 10) should be annotated as [[SomeProduct]] if only products from that lot are sold, or [[IndividualProduct]] if there is only a specific product.
  • A Digital Link that contains a global model number (AI 8013) should be attached to a [[Product]] or a [[ProductModel]].
Other item types should be adapted similarly.

entries.name: schema:hasHealthAspect
entries.description: Indicates the aspect or aspects specifically addressed in some [[HealthTopicContent]]. For example, that the content is an overview, or that it talks about treatment, self-care, treatments or their side-effects.

entries.name: schema:hasMap

entries.name: schema:hasMeasurement

Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

entries.name: schema:hasMenuSection

entries.name: schema:hasMolecularFunction

entries.name: schema:hasTiers

entries.name: schema:hasVariant

entries.name: schema:highPrice
entries.description:
The highest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

entries.name: schema:incentiveAmount
entries.description:
Describes the amount that can be redeemed from this incentive.

[[QuantitativeValue]]: Use this for incentives based on price (either raw amount or percentage-based). For a raw amount example, "You can claim $2,500 - $7,500 from the total cost of installation" would be represented as the following:

{ "@type": "QuantitativeValue", minValue: 2500, maxValue: 7500, "unitCode": "USD" }

[[QuantitivateValue]] can also be used for percentage amounts. In such cases, value is used to represent the incentives percentage, while maxValue represents a limit (if one exists) to that incentive. The unitCode should be 'P1' and the unitText should be '%', while valueReference should be used for holding the currency type. For example, "You can claim up to 30% of the total cost of installation, up to a maximum of $7,500" would be:

{ "@type": "QuantitativeValue", "value": 30, "unitCode": "P1", "unitText": "%", maxValue: 7500, valueReference: USD }

[[UnitPriceSpecification]]: Use this for incentives that are based on amounts rather than price. For example, a net metering rebate that pays $10/kWh, up to $1,000:

{ "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification", "price": 10, "priceCurrency": "USD", "referenceQuantity": 1, "unitCode": "DO3", "unitText": "kw/h", "maxPrice": 1000, "description": "$10 / kwh up to $1000" }

[[LoanOrCredit]]: Use for incentives that are loan based. For example, a loan of $4,000 - $50,000 with a repayment term of 10 years, interest free would look like:

{ "@type": "LoanOrCredit", "loanTerm": { "@type":"QuantitativeValue", "value":"10", "unitCode": "ANN" }, "amount":[ { "@type": "QuantitativeValue", "Name":"fixed interest rate", "value":"0", }, ], "amount":[ { "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "Name":"min loan amount", "value":"4000", "currency":"CAD" }, { "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "Name":"max loan amount", "value":"50000", "currency":"CAD" } ], } In summary:
  • Use [[QuantitativeValue]] for absolute/percentage-based incentives applied on the price of a good/service.
  • Use [[UnitPriceSpecification]] for incentives based on a per-unit basis (e.g. net metering).
  • Use [[LoanOrCredit]] for loans/credits.
.

entries.name: schema:incentiveCompensation

entries.name: schema:incentives
entries.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

entries.name: schema:incentivizedItem
entries.description:
The type or specific product(s) and/or service(s) being incentivized.

DefinedTermSets are used for product and service categories such as the United Nations Standard Products and Services Code:

{ "@type": "DefinedTerm", "inDefinedTermSet": "https://www.unspsc.org/", "termCode": "261315XX", "name": "Photovoltaic module" }

For a specific product or service, use the Product type:

{ "@type": "Product", "name": "Kenmore White 17" Microwave", } For multiple different incentivized items, use multiple [[DefinedTerm]] or [[Product]].

entries.name: schema:includedComposition

entries.name: schema:includedDataCatalog

entries.name: schema:includedInDataCatalog
entries.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

entries.name: schema:includedInHealthInsurancePlan

entries.name: schema:includedRiskFactor

entries.name: schema:includesHealthPlanFormulary

entries.name: schema:includesHealthPlanNetwork

entries.name: schema:includesObject

entries.name: schema:incomeLimit
entries.description:
Optional. Income limit for which the incentive is applicable for.

If MonetaryAmount is specified, this should be based on annualized income (e.g. if an incentive is limited to those making <$114,000 annually):

{ "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "maxValue": 114000, "currency": "USD", } Use Text for incentives that are limited based on other criteria, for example if an incentive is only available to recipients making 120% of the median poverty income in their area.

entries.name: schema:increasesRiskOf

entries.name: schema:industry

entries.name: schema:ineligibleRegion

entries.name: schema:infectiousAgent

entries.name: schema:infectiousAgentClass

entries.name: schema:ingredients

entries.name: schema:inker
entries.description: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.

entries.name: schema:insertion
entries.description: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

entries.name: schema:installUrl
entries.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

entries.name: schema:instructor
entries.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

entries.name: schema:instrument
entries.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

entries.name: schema:intensity
entries.description: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

entries.name: schema:interactingDrug
entries.description: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

entries.name: schema:interactionCount
entries.description: This property is deprecated, alongside the UserInteraction types on which it depended.

entries.name: schema:interactionService
entries.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

entries.name: schema:interactionStatistic
entries.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

entries.name: schema:interactionType
entries.description: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use [[LikeAction]]. For down votes use [[DislikeAction]]. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

entries.name: schema:interactivityType
entries.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

entries.name: schema:interestRate
entries.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

entries.name: schema:interpretedAsClaim
entries.description: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

entries.name: schema:inventoryLevel
entries.description: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

entries.name: schema:inverseOf
entries.description: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

entries.name: schema:isAcceptingNewPatients
entries.description: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

entries.name: schema:isAccessibleForFree
entries.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

entries.name: schema:isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
entries.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

entries.name: schema:isAvailableGenerically
entries.description: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

entries.name: schema:isBasedOn
entries.description: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaptation.

entries.name: schema:isBasedOnUrl
entries.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

entries.name: schema:isConsumableFor
entries.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

entries.name: schema:isEncodedByBioChemEntity
entries.description: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

entries.name: schema:isFamilyFriendly
entries.description: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

entries.description: Indicates whether the offer was accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

entries.name: schema:isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
entries.description: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

entries.name: schema:isLiveBroadcast
entries.description: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

entries.name: schema:isLocatedInSubcellularLocation
entries.description: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

entries.name: schema:isPartOf
entries.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

entries.name: schema:isPartOfBioChemEntity
entries.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

entries.name: schema:isPlanForApartment
entries.description: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

entries.name: schema:isProprietary
entries.description: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

entries.name: schema:isRelatedTo
entries.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

entries.name: schema:isResizable
entries.description: Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

entries.name: schema:isSimilarTo
entries.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

entries.name: schema:isStoreOn
entries.description: The eCommerce marketplace this online store is on.

entries.name: schema:isTierOf
entries.description: The member program this tier is a part of.

entries.name: schema:isUnlabelledFallback
entries.description: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

entries.name: schema:isVariantOf
entries.description: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

entries.name: schema:isbn
entries.description: The ISBN of the book.

entries.name: schema:isicV4
entries.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

entries.name: schema:iso6523Code
entries.description: An organization identifier as defined in [ISO 6523(-1)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO/IEC_6523). The identifier should be in the `XXXX:YYYYYY:ZZZ` or `XXXX:YYYYYY`format. Where `XXXX` is a 4 digit _ICD_ (International Code Designator), `YYYYYY` is an _OID_ (Organization Identifier) with all formatting characters (dots, dashes, spaces) removed with a maximal length of 35 characters, and `ZZZ` is an optional OPI (Organization Part Identifier) with a maximum length of 35 characters. The various components (ICD, OID, OPI) are joined with a colon character (ASCII `0x3a`). Note that many existing organization identifiers defined as attributes like [leiCode](https://schema.org/leiCode) (`0199`), [duns](https://schema.org/duns) (`0060`) or [GLN](https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber) (`0088`) can be expressed using ISO-6523. If possible, ISO-6523 codes should be preferred to populating [vatID](https://schema.org/vatID) or [taxID](https://schema.org/taxID), as ISO identifiers are less ambiguous.

entries.name: schema:isrcCode
entries.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

entries.name: schema:issn
entries.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

entries.name: schema:issueNumber
entries.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

entries.name: schema:issuedBy
entries.description: The organization issuing the item, for example a [[Permit]], [[Ticket]], or [[Certification]].

entries.name: schema:issuedThrough
entries.description: The service through which the permit was granted.

entries.name: schema:iswcCode
entries.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

entries.name: schema:item
entries.description: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

entries.name: schema:itemCondition
entries.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

entries.name: schema:itemDefectReturnFees
entries.description: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

entries.name: schema:itemDefectReturnLabelSource
entries.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a defect product.

entries.name: schema:itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount
entries.description: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

entries.name: schema:itemListElement
entries.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements.  Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

entries.name: schema:itemListOrder
entries.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

entries.name: schema:itemLocation
entries.description: Current location of the item.

entries.name: schema:itemOffered
entries.description: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

entries.name: schema:itemReviewed
entries.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

entries.name: schema:itemShipped
entries.description: Item(s) being shipped.

entries.name: schema:itinerary
entries.description: Destination(s) ( [[Place]] ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use [[ItemList]] to specify that order (see examples).

entries.name: schema:iupacName
entries.description: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

entries.name: schema:jobBenefits
entries.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

entries.name: schema:jobImmediateStart
entries.description: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

entries.name: schema:jobLocation
entries.description: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

entries.name: schema:jobLocationType
entries.description: A description of the job location (e.g. TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

entries.name: schema:jobStartDate
entries.description: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

entries.name: schema:jobTitle
entries.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

entries.name: schema:jurisdiction
entries.description: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

entries.name: schema:keywords
entries.description: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

entries.name: schema:knownVehicleDamages
entries.description: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

entries.name: schema:knows
entries.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

entries.name: schema:knowsAbout
entries.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

entries.name: schema:knowsLanguage
entries.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

entries.name: schema:labelDetails
entries.description: Link to the drug's label details.

entries.name: schema:landlord
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

entries.name: schema:language
