entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

entries.name: schema:lastReviewed
entries.description: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

entries.name: schema:latitude
entries.description: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

entries.name: schema:layoutImage
entries.description: A schematic image showing the floorplan layout.

entries.name: schema:learningResourceType
entries.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

entries.name: schema:leaseLength
entries.description: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

entries.name: schema:legalAddress
entries.description: The legal address of an organization which acts as the officially registered address used for legal and tax purposes. The legal address can be different from the place of operations of a business and other addresses can be part of an organization.

entries.name: schema:legalName
entries.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

entries.name: schema:legalRepresentative
entries.description: One or multiple persons who represent this organization legally such as CEO or sole administrator.

entries.name: schema:legalStatus
entries.description: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

entries.name: schema:legislationAmends
entries.description: Another legislation that this legislation amends, introducing legal changes.

entries.name: schema:legislationApplies
entries.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow transfers another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the legislationTransposes property. For example an informative consolidated law of a European Union's member state "applies" the consolidated version of the European Directive implemented in it.

entries.name: schema:legislationChanges
entries.description: Another legislation that this legislation changes. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, correction, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. The property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the legislationConsolidates property.

entries.name: schema:legislationCommences
entries.description: Another legislation that this one sets into force.

entries.name: schema:legislationConsolidates
entries.description: Indicates another legislation taken into account in this consolidated legislation (which is usually the product of an editorial process that revises the legislation). This property should be used multiple times to refer to both the original version or the previous consolidated version, and to the legislations making the change.

entries.name: schema:legislationCorrects
entries.description: Another legislation in which this one introduces textual changes, like correction of spelling mistakes, with no legal impact (for modifications that have legal impact, use legislationAmends).

entries.name: schema:legislationCountersignedBy
entries.description: The person or organization that countersigned the legislation. Depending on the legal context, a countersignature can indicate that the signed authority undertakes to assume responsibility for texts emanating from a person who is inviolable and irresponsible, (for example a King, Grand Duc or President), or that the authority is in charge of the implementation of the text.

entries.name: schema:legislationDate
entries.description: The date of adoption or signature of the legislation. This is the date at which the text is officially aknowledged to be a legislation, even though it might not even be published or in force.

entries.name: schema:legislationDateOfApplicability
entries.description: The date at which the Legislation becomes applicable. This can sometimes be distinct from the date of entry into force : a text may come in force today, and state it will become applicable in 3 months.

entries.name: schema:legislationDateVersion
entries.description: The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g.: when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

entries.name: schema:legislationEnsuresImplementationOf
entries.description: Indicates that this Legislation ensures the implementation of another Legislation, for example by modifying national legislations so that they do not contradict to an EU regulation or decision. This implies a legal meaning. Transpositions of EU Directive should be captured with legislationTransposes.

entries.name: schema:legislationIdentifier
entries.description: An identifier for the legislation. This can be either a string-based identifier, like the CELEX at EU level or the NOR in France, or a web-based, URL/URI identifier, like an ELI (European Legislation Identifier) or an URN-Lex.

entries.name: schema:legislationJurisdiction
entries.description: The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

entries.name: schema:legislationLegalForce
entries.description: Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

entries.name: schema:legislationLegalValue
entries.description: The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

entries.name: schema:legislationPassedBy
entries.description: The person or organization that originally passed or made the law: typically parliament (for primary legislation) or government (for secondary legislation). This indicates the "legal author" of the law, as opposed to its physical author.

entries.name: schema:legislationRepeals
entries.description: Another legislation that this legislation repeals (cancels, abrogates).

entries.name: schema:legislationResponsible
entries.description: An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

entries.name: schema:legislationTransposes
entries.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of legislation) fulfills the objectives set by another legislation, by passing appropriate implementation measures. Typically, some legislations of European Union's member states or regions transpose European Directives. This indicates a legally binding link between the 2 legislations.

entries.name: schema:legislationType
entries.description: The type of the legislation. Examples of values are "law", "act", "directive", "decree", "regulation", "statutory instrument", "loi organique", "rglement grand-ducal", etc., depending on the country.

entries.name: schema:leiCode
entries.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

entries.name: schema:lender
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

entries.name: schema:lesser
entries.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

entries.name: schema:lesserOrEqual
entries.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

entries.name: schema:letterer
entries.description: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

entries.name: schema:license
entries.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

entries.name: schema:lifeEvent
entries.description: A life event like baptism, communions, Bar Mitzvahs, Aqiqah, Namakarana, Miyamairi, burial, ....

entries.name: schema:line
entries.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

entries.name: schema:linkRelationship
entries.description: Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

entries.name: schema:liveBlogUpdate
entries.description: An update to the LiveBlog.

entries.name: schema:loanMortgageMandateAmount
entries.description: Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

entries.name: schema:loanPaymentAmount
entries.description: The amount of money to pay in a single payment.

entries.name: schema:loanPaymentFrequency
entries.description: Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

entries.name: schema:loanRepaymentForm
entries.description: A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.

entries.name: schema:loanTerm
entries.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

entries.name: schema:loanType
entries.description: The type of a loan or credit.

entries.name: schema:location
entries.description: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

entries.name: schema:locationCreated
entries.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:lodgingUnitDescription
entries.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

entries.name: schema:lodgingUnitType
entries.description: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

entries.name: schema:logo
entries.description: An associated logo.

entries.name: schema:longitude
entries.description: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

entries.name: schema:loser
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

entries.name: schema:lowPrice
entries.description:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

entries.name: schema:lyricist
entries.description: The person who wrote the words.

entries.name: schema:lyrics
entries.description: The words in the song.

entries.name: schema:mainContentOfPage
entries.description: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

entries.name: schema:mainEntity
entries.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:mainEntityOfPage
entries.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

entries.name: schema:maintainer
entries.description: A maintainer of a [[Dataset]], software package ([[SoftwareApplication]]), or other [[Project]]. A maintainer is a [[Person]] or [[Organization]] that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When [[maintainer]] is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a [[Dataset]], it is always  possible that the upstream source has a different maintainer. The [[isBasedOn]] property can be used to indicate such relationships between datasets to make the different maintenance roles clear. Similarly in the case of software, a package may have dedicated maintainers working on integration into software distributions such as Ubuntu, as well as upstream maintainers of the underlying work.

entries.name: schema:makesOffer
entries.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

entries.name: schema:manufacturer
entries.description: The manufacturer of the product.

entries.name: schema:map
entries.description: A URL to a map of the place.

entries.name: schema:mapType
entries.description: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

entries.name: schema:maps
entries.description: A URL to a map of the place.

entries.name: schema:marginOfError
entries.description: A [[marginOfError]] for an [[Observation]].

entries.name: schema:masthead
entries.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

entries.name: schema:material
entries.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

entries.name: schema:materialExtent
entries.description: The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

entries.name: schema:mathExpression
entries.description: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

entries.name: schema:maxPrice
entries.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

entries.name: schema:maxValue
entries.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

entries.name: schema:maximumAttendeeCapacity
entries.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

entries.name: schema:maximumEnrollment
entries.description: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

entries.name: schema:maximumIntake
entries.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

entries.name: schema:maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity
entries.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OfflineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the offline aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

entries.name: schema:maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity
entries.description: The maximum virtual attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OnlineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the online aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

entries.name: schema:mealService
entries.description: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

entries.name: schema:measuredProperty
entries.description: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], typically via its [[StatisticalVariable]]. There are various kinds of applicable [[Property]]: a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems, e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, Data Commons, Wikidata, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

entries.name: schema:measurementDenominator
entries.description: Identifies the denominator variable when an observation represents a ratio or percentage.

entries.name: schema:measurementMethod
entries.description: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

entries.name: schema:measurementQualifier
entries.description: Provides additional qualification to an observation. For example, a GDP observation measures the Nominal value.

entries.name: schema:measurementTechnique
entries.description:
A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabularies and "knowledge graphs". In that case the subproperty of [[variableMeasured]] called [[measuredProperty]] is applicable.
    
The [[measurementTechnique]] property helps when extra clarification is needed about how a [[measuredProperty]] was measured. This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but can often serve as a high level summary for dataset discovery. 

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence". If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory". 

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]]. The value can also be from an enumeration, organized as a [[MeasurementMetholdEnumeration]].

entries.name: schema:mechanismOfAction
entries.description: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

entries.name: schema:mediaAuthenticityCategory
entries.description: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

entries.name: schema:mediaItemAppearance
entries.description: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

entries.name: schema:median
entries.description: The median value.

entries.name: schema:medicalAudience
entries.description: Medical audience for page.

entries.name: schema:medicalSpecialty
entries.description: A medical specialty of the provider.

entries.name: schema:medicineSystem
entries.description: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

entries.name: schema:meetsEmissionStandard
entries.description: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

entries.name: schema:member
entries.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

entries.name: schema:memberOf
entries.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

entries.name: schema:members
entries.description: A member of this organization.

entries.name: schema:membershipNumber
entries.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

entries.name: schema:membershipPointsEarned
entries.description: The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (E.g. stars, miles, etc.)

entries.name: schema:memoryRequirements
entries.description: Minimum memory requirements.

entries.name: schema:mentions
entries.description: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

entries.name: schema:menu
entries.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

entries.name: schema:menuAddOn
entries.description: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

entries.name: schema:merchant
entries.description: 'merchant' is an out-dated term for 'seller'.

entries.name: schema:merchantReturnDays
entries.description: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

entries.name: schema:merchantReturnLink
entries.description: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

entries.name: schema:messageAttachment
entries.description: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

entries.name: schema:mileageFromOdometer
entries.description: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles.

entries.name: schema:minPrice
entries.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

entries.name: schema:minValue
entries.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

entries.name: schema:minimumPaymentDue
entries.description: The minimum payment required at this time.

entries.name: schema:missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
entries.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

entries.name: schema:mobileUrl
entries.description:
The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'.

To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing environments. Pages and sites referenced with the long-established [[url]] property should ideally also be usable on a wide variety of devices, including mobile phones. In most cases, it would be pointless and counter productive to attempt to update all [[url]] markup to use [[mobileUrl]] for more mobile-oriented pages. The property is intended for the case when items (primarily [[Product]] and [[Offer]]) have extra URLs hosted on an additional "mobile site" alongside the main one. It should not be taken as an endorsement of this publication style.

entries.name: schema:model
entries.description: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

entries.name: schema:modelDate
entries.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

entries.name: schema:modifiedTime
entries.description: The date and time the reservation was modified.

entries.name: schema:molecularFormula
entries.description: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

entries.name: schema:molecularWeight
entries.description: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

entries.name: schema:monoisotopicMolecularWeight
entries.description: The monoisotopic mass is the sum of the masses of the atoms in a molecule using the unbound, ground-state, rest mass of the principal (most abundant) isotope for each element instead of the isotopic average mass. Please include the units in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '770.230488 g/mol' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

entries.name: schema:monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount
entries.description: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

entries.name: schema:monthsOfExperience
entries.description: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

entries.name: schema:mpn
entries.description: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

entries.name: schema:multipleValues
entries.description: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

entries.name: schema:muscleAction
entries.description: The movement the muscle generates.

entries.name: schema:musicArrangement
entries.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

entries.name: schema:musicBy
entries.description: The composer of the soundtrack.

entries.name: schema:musicCompositionForm
entries.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

entries.name: schema:musicGroupMember
entries.description: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

entries.name: schema:musicReleaseFormat
entries.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

entries.name: schema:musicalKey
entries.description: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

entries.name: schema:naics
entries.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

entries.name: schema:name
entries.description: The name of the item.

entries.name: schema:namedPosition
entries.description: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

entries.name: schema:nationality
entries.description: Nationality of the person.

entries.name: schema:naturalProgression
entries.description: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

entries.name: schema:negativeNotes
entries.description:
Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry 

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions 
tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[negativeNotes]] can be used on [[Product]].

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most negative is at the beginning of the list).

entries.name: schema:nerve
entries.description: The underlying innervation associated with the muscle.

entries.name: schema:nerveMotor
entries.description: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

entries.name: schema:netWorth
entries.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting the total value of liabilities from the total value of assets.

entries.name: schema:newsUpdatesAndGuidelines
entries.description: Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing [[SpecialAnnouncement]] markup on a site.

entries.name: schema:nextItem
entries.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

entries.name: schema:noBylinesPolicy
entries.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

entries.name: schema:nonEqual
entries.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

entries.name: schema:nonProprietaryName
entries.description: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

entries.name: schema:nonprofitStatus
entries.description: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

entries.name: schema:normalRange
entries.description: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

entries.name: schema:nsn
entries.description: Indicates the [NATO stock number](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NATO_Stock_Number) (nsn) of a [[Product]].

entries.name: schema:numAdults
entries.description: The number of adults staying in the unit.

entries.name: schema:numChildren
entries.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

entries.name: schema:numConstraints
entries.description: Indicates the number of constraints property values defined for a particular [[ConstraintNode]] such as [[StatisticalVariable]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalVariable]] or other construct that is defined using properties on template-style nodes.

entries.name: schema:numItems
entries.description: Limits the number of items being shipped for which these conditions apply.

entries.name: schema:numTracks
entries.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

entries.name: schema:numberOfAccommodationUnits
entries.description: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

entries.name: schema:numberOfAirbags
entries.description: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

entries.name: schema:numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
entries.description: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

entries.name: schema:numberOfAxles
entries.description: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

entries.name: schema:numberOfBathroomsTotal
entries.description: The total integer number of bathrooms in some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

entries.name: schema:numberOfBedrooms
entries.description: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

entries.name: schema:numberOfBeds
entries.description: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

entries.name: schema:numberOfCredits
entries.description: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

entries.name: schema:numberOfDoors
entries.description: The number of doors.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

entries.name: schema:numberOfEmployees
entries.description: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.

entries.name: schema:numberOfEpisodes
entries.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

entries.name: schema:numberOfForwardGears
entries.description: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

entries.name: schema:numberOfFullBathrooms
entries.description: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and  bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

entries.name: schema:numberOfItems
entries.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

entries.name: schema:numberOfLoanPayments
entries.description: The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

entries.name: schema:numberOfPages
entries.description: The number of pages in the book.

entries.name: schema:numberOfPartialBathrooms
entries.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and  bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

entries.name: schema:numberOfPlayers
entries.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

entries.name: schema:numberOfPreviousOwners
entries.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

entries.name: schema:numberOfRooms
entries.description:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

entries.name: schema:numberOfSeasons
entries.description: The number of seasons in this series.

entries.name: schema:numberedPosition
entries.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

entries.name: schema:nutrition
entries.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

entries.name: schema:object
entries.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

entries.name: schema:observationAbout
entries.description: The [[observationAbout]] property identifies an entity, often a [[Place]], associated with an [[Observation]].

entries.name: schema:observationDate
entries.description: The observationDate of an [[Observation]].

entries.name: schema:observationPeriod
entries.description: The length of time an Observation took place over. The format follows `P[0-9]*[Y|M|D|h|m|s]`. For example, P1Y is Period 1 Year, P3M is Period 3 Months, P3h is Period 3 hours.

entries.name: schema:occupancy
entries.description:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person.

entries.name: schema:occupationLocation
entries.description: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

entries.name: schema:occupationalCategory
entries.description:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

entries.name: schema:occupationalCredentialAwarded
entries.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

entries.name: schema:offerCount
entries.description: The number of offers for the product.

entries.name: schema:offeredBy
entries.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

entries.name: schema:offers
entries.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

entries.name: schema:offersPrescriptionByMail
entries.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

entries.name: schema:openingHours
entries.description: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

entries.name: schema:openingHoursSpecification
entries.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

entries.name: schema:opens
entries.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

entries.name: schema:operatingSystem
entries.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OS X 10.6, Android 1.6).

entries.name: schema:opponent
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

entries.name: schema:option
entries.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

entries.name: schema:orderDate
entries.description: Date order was placed.

entries.name: schema:orderDelivery
entries.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

entries.name: schema:orderItemNumber
entries.description: The identifier of the order item.

entries.name: schema:orderItemStatus
entries.description: The current status of the order item.

entries.name: schema:orderNumber
entries.description: The identifier of the transaction.

entries.name: schema:orderPercentage
entries.description: Value in the range [0.0 ; 1.0] representing the fraction of the value of the order that is charged as shipping cost.

entries.name: schema:orderQuantity
entries.description: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

entries.name: schema:orderStatus
entries.description: The current status of the order.

entries.name: schema:orderValue
entries.description: Minimum and maximum order value for which these shipping conditions are valid.

entries.name: schema:orderedItem
entries.description: The item ordered.

entries.name: schema:organizer
entries.description: An organizer of an Event.

entries.name: schema:originAddress
entries.description: Shipper's address.

entries.name: schema:originalMediaContextDescription
entries.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

entries.name: schema:originalMediaLink
entries.description: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

entries.name: schema:originatesFrom
entries.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

entries.name: schema:overdosage
entries.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

entries.name: schema:ownedFrom
entries.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

entries.name: schema:ownedThrough
entries.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

entries.name: schema:owner
entries.description: A person or organization who owns this Thing.

entries.name: schema:ownershipFundingInfo
entries.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

entries.name: schema:owns
entries.description: Things owned by the organization or person.

entries.name: schema:pageEnd
entries.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

entries.name: schema:pageStart
entries.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

entries.name: schema:pagination
entries.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

entries.name: schema:parent
entries.description: A parent of this person.

entries.name: schema:parentItem
entries.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general. Typically used for Q/A discussion threads e.g. a chain of comments with the first comment being an [[Article]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. See also [[comment]] which points from something to a comment about it.

entries.name: schema:parentOrganization
entries.description: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

entries.name: schema:parentService
entries.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

entries.name: schema:parentTaxon
entries.description: Closest parent taxon of the taxon in question.

entries.name: schema:parents
entries.description: A parents of the person.

entries.name: schema:partOfEpisode
entries.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

entries.name: schema:partOfInvoice
entries.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

entries.name: schema:partOfOrder
entries.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

entries.name: schema:partOfSeason
entries.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

entries.name: schema:partOfSeries
entries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

entries.name: schema:partOfSystem
entries.description: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

entries.name: schema:partOfTVSeries
entries.description: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

entries.name: schema:partOfTrip
entries.description: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

entries.name: schema:participant
entries.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

entries.name: schema:partySize
entries.description: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

entries.name: schema:passengerPriorityStatus
entries.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

entries.name: schema:passengerSequenceNumber
entries.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

entries.name: schema:pathophysiology
entries.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

entries.name: schema:pattern
entries.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

entries.name: schema:payload
entries.description:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:paymentAccepted
entries.description: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

entries.name: schema:paymentDue
entries.description: The date that payment is due.

entries.name: schema:paymentDueDate
entries.description: The date that payment is due.

entries.name: schema:paymentMethod
entries.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

entries.name: schema:paymentMethodId
entries.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

entries.name: schema:paymentMethodType
entries.description: The type of a payment method.

entries.name: schema:paymentStatus
entries.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

entries.name: schema:paymentUrl
entries.description: The URL for sending a payment.

entries.name: schema:penciler
entries.description: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

entries.name: schema:percentile10
entries.description: The 10th percentile value.

entries.name: schema:percentile25
entries.description: The 25th percentile value.

entries.name: schema:percentile75
entries.description: The 75th percentile value.

entries.name: schema:percentile90
entries.description: The 90th percentile value.

entries.name: schema:performTime
entries.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

entries.name: schema:performer
entries.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

entries.name: schema:performerIn
entries.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

entries.name: schema:performers
entries.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

entries.name: schema:permissionType
entries.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

entries.name: schema:permissions
entries.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

entries.name: schema:permitAudience
entries.description: The target audience for this permit.

entries.name: schema:permittedUsage
entries.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

entries.name: schema:petsAllowed
entries.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

entries.name: schema:phoneticText
entries.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /hjustn/.

entries.name: schema:photo
entries.description: A photograph of this place.

entries.name: schema:photos
entries.description: Photographs of this place.

entries.name: schema:physicalRequirement
entries.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

entries.name: schema:physiologicalBenefits
entries.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

entries.name: schema:pickupLocation
entries.description: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

entries.name: schema:pickupTime
entries.description: When a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

entries.name: schema:playMode
entries.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

entries.name: schema:playerType
entries.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

entries.name: schema:playersOnline
entries.description: Number of players on the server.

entries.name: schema:polygon
entries.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

entries.name: schema:populationType
entries.description: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]] or all cases within the scope of a [[StatisticalVariable]].

entries.name: position
entries.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

entries.name: schema:positiveNotes
entries.description:
Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).

entries.name: schema:possibleComplication
entries.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

entries.name: schema:possibleTreatment
entries.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

entries.name: schema:postOfficeBoxNumber
entries.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

entries.name: schema:postOp
entries.description: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

entries.name: schema:postalCode
entries.description: The postal code. For example, 94043.

entries.name: schema:postalCodeBegin
entries.description: First postal code in a range (included).

entries.name: schema:postalCodeEnd
entries.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

entries.name: schema:postalCodePrefix
entries.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

entries.name: schema:postalCodeRange
entries.description: A defined range of postal codes.

entries.name: schema:potentialAction
entries.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

entries.name: schema:potentialUse
entries.description: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

entries.name: schema:practicesAt
entries.description: A [[MedicalOrganization]] where the [[IndividualPhysician]] practices.

entries.name: schema:preOp
entries.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

entries.name: schema:predecessorOf
entries.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

entries.name: schema:pregnancyCategory
entries.description: Pregnancy category of this drug.

entries.name: schema:pregnancyWarning
entries.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

entries.name: schema:prepTime
entries.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

entries.name: schema:preparation
entries.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

entries.name: schema:prescribingInfo
entries.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

entries.name: schema:prescriptionStatus
entries.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription, e.g. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

entries.name: schema:previousItem
entries.description: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.

entries.name: schema:previousStartDate
entries.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

entries.name: schema:price
entries.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

entries.name: schema:priceComponent
entries.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

entries.name: schema:priceComponentType
entries.description: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

entries.name: schema:priceCurrency
entries.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

entries.name: schema:priceRange
entries.description: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

entries.name: schema:priceSpecification
entries.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

entries.name: schema:priceType
entries.description: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or, a UN/EDIFACT 5387 code, or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEnumeration.

entries.name: schema:priceValidUntil
entries.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

entries.name: schema:primaryImageOfPage
entries.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

entries.name: schema:primaryPrevention
entries.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

entries.name: schema:printColumn
entries.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

entries.name: schema:printEdition
entries.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

entries.name: schema:printPage
entries.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

entries.name: schema:printSection
entries.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

entries.name: schema:procedure
entries.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

entries.name: schema:procedureType
entries.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

entries.name: schema:processingTime
entries.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

entries.name: schema:processorRequirements
entries.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

entries.name: schema:producer
entries.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, TV/radio series etc.).

entries.name: schema:produces
entries.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

entries.name: schema:productGroupID
entries.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

entries.name: schema:productID
entries.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

entries.name: schema:productSupported
entries.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

entries.name: schema:productionCompany
entries.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

entries.name: schema:productionDate
entries.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

entries.name: schema:proficiencyLevel
entries.description: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

entries.name: schema:program
entries.description: The [MemberProgram](https://schema.org/MemberProgram) associated with a [ProgramMembership](https://schema.org/ProgramMembership).

entries.name: schema:programMembershipUsed
entries.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

entries.name: schema:programName
entries.description: The program providing the membership. It is preferable to use [:program](https://schema.org/program) instead.

entries.name: schema:programPrerequisites
entries.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

entries.name: schema:programType
entries.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

entries.name: schema:programmingLanguage
entries.description: The computer programming language.

entries.name: schema:programmingModel
entries.description: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

entries.name: schema:pronouns
entries.description:
A short string listing or describing pronouns for a person. Typically the person concerned is the best authority as pronouns are a critical part of personal identity and expression. Publishers and consumers of this information are reminded to treat this data responsibly, take country-specific laws related to gender expression into account, and be wary of out-of-date data and drawing unwarranted inferences about the person being described.

In English, formulations such as "they/them", "she/her", and "he/him" are commonly used online and can also be used here. We do not intend to enumerate all possible micro-syntaxes in all languages. More structured and well-defined external values for pronouns can be referenced using the [[StructuredValue]] or [[DefinedTerm]] values.

entries.name: schema:propertyID
entries.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific ID of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

entries.name: schema:proprietaryName
entries.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

entries.name: schema:proteinContent
entries.description: The number of grams of protein.

entries.name: schema:provider
entries.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

entries.name: schema:providerMobility
entries.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

entries.name: schema:providesBroadcastService
entries.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

entries.name: schema:providesService
entries.description: The service provided by this channel.

entries.name: schema:publicAccess
entries.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value.

entries.name: schema:publicTransportClosuresInfo
entries.description: Information about public transport closures.

entries.name: schema:publication
entries.description: A publication event associated with the item.

entries.name: schema:publicationType
entries.description: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).

entries.name: schema:publishedBy
entries.description: An agent associated with the publication event.

entries.name: schema:publishedOn
entries.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

entries.name: schema:publisher
entries.description: The publisher of the article in question.

entries.name: schema:publisherImprint
entries.description: The publishing division which published the comic.

entries.name: schema:publishingPrinciples
entries.description:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

entries.name: schema:purchaseDate
entries.description: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

entries.name: schema:purchasePriceLimit
entries.description: Optional. The maximum price the item can have and still qualify for this offer.

entries.name: schema:purchaseType
entries.description: Optional. The type of purchase the consumer must make in order to qualify for this incentive.

entries.name: schema:qualifications
entries.description: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

entries.name: schema:qualifiedExpense
entries.description: Optional. The types of expenses that are covered by the incentive. For example some incentives are only for the goods (tangible items) but the services (labor) are excluded.

entries.name: schema:quarantineGuidelines
entries.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

entries.name: schema:query
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

entries.name: schema:quest
entries.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

entries.name: schema:question
entries.description: A sub property of object. A question.

entries.name: schema:rangeIncludes
entries.description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

entries.name: schema:ratingCount
entries.description: The count of total number of ratings.

entries.name: schema:ratingExplanation
entries.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

entries.name: schema:ratingValue
entries.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

entries.name: schema:readBy
entries.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

entries.name: schema:readonlyValue
entries.description: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

entries.name: schema:realEstateAgent
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

entries.name: schema:recipe
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

entries.name: schema:recipeCategory
entries.description: The category of the recipefor example, appetizer, entree, etc.

entries.name: schema:recipeCuisine
entries.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

entries.name: schema:recipeIngredient
entries.description: An ingredient or ordered list of ingredients and potentially quantities used in the recipe, e.g. 1 cup of sugar, flour or garlic.  The ingredients can be represented as free text or more structured values.

entries.name: schema:recipeInstructions
entries.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

entries.name: schema:recipeYield
entries.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

entries.name: schema:recipient
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

entries.name: schema:recognizedBy
entries.description: An organization that acknowledges the validity, value or utility of a credential. Note: recognition may include a process of quality assurance or accreditation.

entries.name: schema:recognizingAuthority
entries.description: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

entries.name: schema:recommendationStrength
entries.description: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

entries.name: schema:recommendedIntake
entries.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

entries.name: schema:recordLabel
entries.description: The label that issued the release.

entries.name: schema:recordedAs
entries.description: An audio recording of the work.

entries.name: schema:recordedAt
entries.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

entries.name: schema:recordedIn
entries.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

entries.name: schema:recordingOf
entries.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

entries.name: schema:recourseLoan
entries.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

entries.name: schema:referee
entries.description: An official who watches a game or match closely to enforce the rules and arbitrate on matters arising from the play such as referees, umpires or judges. The name of the effective function can vary according to the sport.

entries.name: schema:referenceQuantity
entries.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

entries.name: schema:referencesOrder
entries.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

entries.name: schema:refundType
entries.description: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

entries.name: schema:regionDrained
entries.description: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

entries.name: schema:regionsAllowed
entries.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

entries.name: schema:relatedAnatomy
entries.description: Anatomical systems or structures that relate to the superficial anatomy.

entries.name: schema:relatedCondition
entries.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

entries.name: schema:relatedDrug
entries.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

entries.name: schema:relatedLink
entries.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

entries.name: schema:relatedStructure
entries.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

entries.name: schema:relatedTherapy
entries.description: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

entries.name: schema:relatedTo
entries.description: The most generic familial relation.

entries.name: schema:releaseDate
entries.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

entries.name: schema:releaseNotes
entries.description: Description of what changed in this version.

entries.name: schema:releaseOf
entries.description: The album this is a release of.

entries.name: schema:releasedEvent
entries.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

entries.name: schema:relevantOccupation
entries.description: The Occupation for the JobPosting.

entries.name: schema:relevantSpecialty
entries.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

entries.name: schema:remainingAttendeeCapacity
entries.description: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

entries.name: schema:renegotiableLoan
entries.description: Whether the terms for payment of interest can be renegotiated during the life of the loan.

entries.name: schema:repeatCount
entries.description: Defines the number of times a recurring [[Event]] will take place.

entries.name: schema:repeatFrequency
entries.description:
Defines the frequency at which [[Event]]s will occur according to a schedule [[Schedule]]. The intervals between
      events should be defined as a [[Duration]] of time.

entries.name: schema:repetitions
entries.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

entries.name: schema:replacee
entries.description: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

entries.name: schema:replacer
entries.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

entries.name: schema:replyToUrl
entries.description: The URL at which a reply may be posted to the specified UserComment.

entries.name: schema:reportNumber
entries.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

entries.name: schema:representativeOfPage
entries.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

entries.name: schema:requiredCollateral
entries.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

entries.name: schema:requiredGender
entries.description: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

entries.name: schema:requiredMaxAge
entries.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

entries.name: schema:requiredMinAge
entries.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

entries.name: schema:requiredQuantity
entries.description: The required quantity of the item(s).

entries.name: schema:requirements
entries.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

entries.name: schema:requiresSubscription
entries.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

entries.name: schema:reservationFor
entries.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

entries.name: schema:reservationId
entries.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

entries.name: schema:reservationStatus
entries.description: The current status of the reservation.

entries.name: schema:reservedTicket
entries.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

entries.name: schema:responsibilities
entries.description: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

entries.name: schema:restPeriods
entries.description: How often one should break from the activity.

entries.name: schema:restockingFee
entries.description: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

entries.name: schema:result
entries.description: The result produced in the action. E.g. John wrote *a book*.

entries.name: schema:resultComment
entries.description: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

entries.name: schema:resultReview
entries.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

entries.name: schema:returnFees
entries.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason).

entries.name: schema:returnLabelSource
entries.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

entries.name: schema:returnMethod
entries.description: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

entries.name: schema:returnPolicyCategory
entries.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

entries.name: schema:returnPolicyCountry
entries.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent to.

entries.name: schema:returnPolicySeasonalOverride
entries.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

entries.name: schema:returnShippingFeesAmount
entries.description: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

entries.name: schema:review
entries.description: A review of the item.

entries.name: schema:reviewAspect
entries.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

entries.name: schema:reviewBody
entries.description: The actual body of the review.

entries.name: schema:reviewCount
entries.description: The count of total number of reviews.

entries.name: schema:reviewRating
entries.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

entries.name: schema:reviewedBy
entries.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

entries.name: schema:reviews
entries.description: Review of the item.

entries.name: schema:riskFactor
entries.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

entries.name: schema:risks
entries.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

entries.name: schema:roleName
entries.description: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

entries.name: schema:roofLoad
entries.description:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:rsvpResponse
entries.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

entries.name: schema:runsTo
