entries.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

entries.name: schema:runtime
entries.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

entries.name: schema:runtimePlatform
entries.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

entries.name: schema:rxcui
entries.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

entries.name: schema:safetyConsideration
entries.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

entries.name: schema:salaryCurrency
entries.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

entries.name: schema:salaryUponCompletion
entries.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

entries.name: schema:sameAs
entries.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

entries.name: schema:sampleType
entries.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

entries.name: schema:saturatedFatContent
entries.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

entries.name: schema:scheduleTimezone
entries.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

entries.name: schema:scheduledPaymentDate
entries.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

entries.name: schema:scheduledTime
entries.description: The time the object is scheduled to.

entries.name: schema:schemaVersion
entries.description:
Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to
    indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explored in the community.

entries.name: schema:schoolClosuresInfo
entries.description: Information about school closures.

entries.name: schema:screenCount
entries.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

entries.name: schema:screenshot
entries.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

entries.name: schema:sdDatePublished
entries.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]].

entries.name: schema:sdLicense
entries.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

entries.name: schema:sdPublisher
entries.description:
Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The
[[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

entries.name: schema:season
entries.description: A season in a media series.

entries.name: schema:seasonNumber
entries.description: Position of the season within an ordered group of seasons.

entries.name: schema:seasonalOverride
entries.description: Limited period during which these shipping conditions apply.

entries.name: schema:seasons
entries.description: A season in a media series.

entries.name: schema:seatNumber
entries.description: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

entries.name: schema:seatRow
entries.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

entries.name: schema:seatSection
entries.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

entries.name: schema:seatingCapacity
entries.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

entries.name: schema:seatingType
entries.description: The type/class of the seat.

entries.name: schema:secondaryPrevention
entries.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

entries.name: schema:securityClearanceRequirement
entries.description: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

entries.name: schema:securityScreening
entries.description: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

entries.name: schema:seeks

entries.name: schema:seller

entries.name: schema:sender
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

entries.name: schema:sensoryRequirement
entries.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

entries.name: schema:sensoryUnit

entries.name: schema:serialNumber
entries.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

entries.name: schema:seriousAdverseOutcome

Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

entries.name: schema:serverStatus

entries.name: schema:servesCuisine
entries.description: The cuisine of the restaurant.

entries.name: schema:serviceArea
entries.description: The geographic area where the service is provided.

entries.name: schema:serviceAudience
entries.description: The audience eligible for this service.

entries.name: schema:serviceLocation
entries.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

entries.name: schema:serviceOperator
entries.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

entries.name: schema:serviceOutput
entries.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

entries.name: schema:servicePhone
entries.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

entries.name: schema:servicePostalAddress
entries.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

entries.name: schema:serviceSmsNumber
entries.description: The number to access the service by text message.

entries.name: schema:serviceType

entries.name: schema:serviceUrl
entries.description: The website to access the service.

entries.name: schema:servingSize
entries.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

entries.name: schema:sha256
entries.description: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'.

entries.name: schema:sharedContent
entries.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

entries.name: schema:shippingConditions
entries.description: The conditions (constraints, price) applicable to the [[ShippingService]].

entries.name: schema:shippingDestination
entries.description: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways, e.g. postalCode ranges.

entries.name: schema:shippingDetails
entries.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

entries.name: schema:shippingOrigin
entries.description: Indicates the origin of a shipment, i.e. where it should be coming from.

entries.name: schema:shippingRate
entries.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

entries.name: schema:sibling
entries.description: A sibling of the person.

entries.name: schema:siblings
entries.description: A sibling of the person.

entries.name: schema:signDetected
entries.description: A sign detected by the test.

entries.name: schema:signOrSymptom
entries.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

entries.name: schema:significance
entries.description: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

entries.name: schema:significantLink
entries.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

entries.name: schema:significantLinks
entries.description: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

entries.name: schema:size
entries.description: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

entries.name: schema:sizeGroup
entries.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular".

entries.name: schema:sizeSystem
entries.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

entries.name: schema:skills
entries.description: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is either claimed by a person, an organization or desired or required to fulfill a role or to work in an occupation.

entries.name: schema:sku
entries.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

entries.name: schema:slogan
entries.description: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

entries.name: schema:smiles
entries.description: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings.  Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

entries.name: schema:smokingAllowed
entries.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

entries.name: schema:sodiumContent
entries.description: The number of milligrams of sodium.

entries.name: schema:softwareAddOn
entries.description: Additional content for a software application.

entries.name: schema:softwareHelp
entries.description: Software application help.

entries.name: schema:softwareRequirements
entries.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

entries.name: schema:softwareVersion
entries.description: Version of the software instance.

entries.name: schema:source
entries.description: The source or cause of the event.

entries.name: schema:sourceOrganization
entries.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

entries.name: schema:sourcedFrom
entries.description: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

entries.name: schema:spatial
entries.description:
The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties
(e.g. [[locationCreated]], [[spatialCoverage]], [[contentLocation]]) are not known to be appropriate.

entries.name: schema:spatialCoverage
entries.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

entries.name: schema:speakable
entries.description:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.

3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.


For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this
we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

entries.name: schema:specialCommitments
entries.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

entries.name: schema:specialOpeningHoursSpecification
entries.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

entries.name: schema:specialty
entries.description: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

entries.name: schema:speechToTextMarkup
entries.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

entries.name: schema:speed
entries.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

entries.name: schema:spokenByCharacter
entries.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:sponsor
entries.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

entries.name: schema:sport
entries.description: A type of sport (e.g. Baseball).

entries.name: schema:sportsActivityLocation
entries.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

entries.name: schema:sportsEvent
entries.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

entries.name: schema:sportsTeam
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

entries.name: schema:spouse
entries.description: The person's spouse.

entries.name: schema:stage
entries.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

entries.name: schema:stageAsNumber
entries.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

entries.name: schema:starRating
entries.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

entries.name: schema:startDate
entries.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

entries.name: schema:startOffset
entries.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

entries.name: schema:startTime
entries.description: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

entries.name: schema:statType
entries.description: Indicates the kind of statistic represented by a [[StatisticalVariable]], e.g. mean, count etc. The value of statType is a property, either from within Schema.org (e.g. [[median]], [[marginOfError]], [[maxValue]], [[minValue]]) or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

entries.name: schema:status
entries.description: The status of the study (enumerated).

entries.name: schema:steeringPosition
entries.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

entries.name: schema:step
entries.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

entries.name: schema:stepValue
entries.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

entries.name: schema:steps
entries.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

entries.name: schema:storageRequirements
entries.description: Storage requirements (free space required).

entries.name: schema:streetAddress
entries.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

entries.name: schema:strengthUnit
entries.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

entries.name: schema:strengthValue
entries.description: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

entries.name: schema:structuralClass
entries.description: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

entries.name: schema:study
entries.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

entries.name: schema:studyDesign
entries.description: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

entries.name: schema:studyLocation
entries.description: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

entries.name: schema:studySubject
entries.description: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

entries.name: schema:subEvent
entries.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

entries.name: schema:subEvents
entries.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

entries.name: schema:subOrganization
entries.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

entries.name: schema:subReservation
entries.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

entries.name: schema:subStageSuffix
entries.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

entries.name: schema:subStructure
entries.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

entries.name: schema:subTest
entries.description: A component test of the panel.

entries.name: schema:subTrip
entries.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

entries.name: schema:subjectOf
entries.description: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

entries.name: schema:subtitleLanguage
entries.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

entries.name: schema:successorOf
entries.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

entries.name: schema:sugarContent
entries.description: The number of grams of sugar.

entries.name: schema:suggestedAge
entries.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

entries.name: schema:suggestedAnswer
entries.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

entries.name: schema:suggestedGender
entries.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

entries.name: schema:suggestedMaxAge
entries.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

entries.name: schema:suggestedMeasurement
entries.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

entries.name: schema:suggestedMinAge
entries.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

entries.name: schema:suitableForDiet
entries.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

entries.name: schema:superEvent
entries.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

entries.name: schema:supersededBy
entries.description: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

entries.name: schema:supply
entries.description: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

entries.name: schema:supplyTo
entries.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

entries.name: schema:supportingData
entries.description: Supporting data for a SoftwareApplication.

entries.name: schema:surface
entries.description: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

entries.name: schema:syllabusSections
entries.description: Indicates (typically several) Syllabus entities that lay out what each section of the overall course will cover.

entries.name: schema:target
entries.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint, or url, for an Action.

entries.name: schema:targetCollection
entries.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

entries.name: schema:targetDescription
entries.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

entries.name: schema:targetName
entries.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

entries.name: schema:targetPlatform
entries.description: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

entries.name: schema:targetPopulation
entries.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

entries.name: schema:targetProduct
entries.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

entries.name: schema:targetUrl
entries.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

entries.name: schema:taxID
entries.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

entries.name: schema:taxonRank
entries.description: The taxonomic rank of this taxon given preferably as a URI from a controlled vocabulary  typically the ranks from TDWG TaxonRank ontology or equivalent Wikidata URIs.

entries.name: schema:taxonomicRange
entries.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

entries.name: schema:teaches
entries.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

entries.name: schema:telephone
entries.description: The telephone number.

entries.name: schema:temporal
entries.description:
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties
(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

entries.name: schema:temporalCoverage
entries.description:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In
      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode, may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL.
      Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.

entries.name: schema:termCode
entries.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]].

entries.name: schema:termDuration
entries.description: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

entries.name: schema:termsOfService
entries.description: Human-readable terms of service documentation.

entries.name: schema:termsPerYear
entries.description: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

entries.name: schema:text
entries.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

entries.name: schema:textValue
entries.description: Text value being annotated.

entries.name: schema:thumbnail
entries.description: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

entries.name: schema:thumbnailUrl
entries.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

entries.name: schema:tickerSymbol
entries.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO 15022.

entries.name: schema:ticketNumber
entries.description: The unique identifier for the ticket.

entries.name: schema:ticketToken
entries.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

entries.name: schema:ticketedSeat
entries.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

entries.name: schema:timeOfDay
entries.description: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

entries.name: schema:timeRequired
entries.description: Approximate or typical time it usually takes to work with or through the content of this work for the typical or target audience.

entries.name: schema:timeToComplete
entries.description: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

entries.name: schema:timestamp
entries.description: The instant the event occured.

entries.name: schema:tissueSample
entries.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

entries.name: schema:title
entries.description: The title of the job.

entries.name: schema:titleEIDR
entries.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]].

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]], [[TVEpisode]], [[TVSeason]], and [[TVSeries]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

entries.name: schema:toLocation
entries.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

entries.name: schema:toRecipient
entries.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

entries.name: schema:tocContinuation
entries.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

entries.name: schema:tocEntry
entries.description: Indicates a [[HyperTocEntry]] in a [[HyperToc]].

entries.name: schema:tongueWeight
entries.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR).

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:tool
entries.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

entries.name: schema:torque
entries.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch

* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:totalHistoricalEnrollment
entries.description: The total number of students that have enrolled in the history of the course.

entries.name: schema:totalJobOpenings
entries.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

entries.name: schema:totalPaymentDue
entries.description: The total amount due.

entries.name: schema:totalPrice
entries.description:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

entries.name: schema:totalTime
entries.description: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

entries.name: schema:tourBookingPage
entries.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

entries.name: schema:touristType
entries.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. E.g. children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

entries.name: schema:track
entries.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

entries.name: schema:trackingNumber
entries.description: Shipper tracking number.

entries.name: schema:trackingUrl
entries.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

entries.name: schema:tracks
entries.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

entries.name: schema:trailer
entries.description: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

entries.name: schema:trailerWeight
entries.description:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:trainName
entries.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

entries.name: schema:trainNumber
entries.description: The unique identifier for the train.

entries.name: schema:trainingSalary
entries.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

entries.name: schema:transFatContent
entries.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

entries.name: schema:transcript
entries.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

entries.name: schema:transitTime
entries.description:
The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer.

  In the context of [[ShippingDeliveryTime]], use the [[QuantitativeValue]]. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

  In the context of [[ShippingConditions]], use the [[ServicePeriod]]. It has a duration (as a [[QuantitativeValue]]) and also business days and a cut-off time.

entries.name: schema:translationOfWork
entries.description: The work that this work has been translated from. E.g.  is a translationOf On the Origin of Species.

entries.name: schema:translator
entries.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

entries.name: schema:transmissionMethod
entries.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

entries.name: schema:travelBans
entries.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

entries.name: schema:trialDesign
entries.description: Specifics about the trial design (enumerated).

entries.name: schema:tributary
entries.description: The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

entries.name: schema:tripOrigin
entries.description: The location of origin of the trip, prior to any destination(s).

entries.name: schema:typeOfBed
entries.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

entries.name: schema:typeOfGood
entries.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

entries.name: schema:typicalAgeRange
entries.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

entries.name: schema:typicalCreditsPerTerm
entries.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

entries.name: schema:typicalTest
entries.description: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

entries.name: schema:underName
entries.description: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

entries.name: schema:unitCode
entries.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

entries.name: schema:unitText
entries.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

entries.name: schema:unnamedSourcesPolicy
entries.description: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

entries.name: schema:unsaturatedFatContent
entries.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

entries.name: schema:uploadDate
entries.description: Date (including time if available) when this media object was uploaded to this site.

entries.name: schema:upvoteCount
entries.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

entries.name: schema:url
entries.description: URL of the item.

entries.name: schema:urlTemplate
entries.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

entries.name: schema:usNPI
entries.description: A National Provider Identifier (NPI) is a unique 10-digit identification number issued to health care providers in the United States by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.

entries.name: schema:usageInfo
entries.description:
The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information, e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options.

This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

entries.name: schema:usedToDiagnose
entries.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

entries.name: schema:userInteractionCount
entries.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

entries.name: schema:usesDevice
entries.description: Device used to perform the test.

entries.name: schema:usesHealthPlanIdStandard
entries.description: The standard for interpreting the Plan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

entries.name: schema:utterances
entries.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

entries.name: schema:validFor
entries.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

entries.name: schema:validForMemberTier
entries.description: The membership program tier an Offer (or a PriceSpecification, OfferShippingDetails, or MerchantReturnPolicy under an Offer) is valid for.

entries.name: validFrom
entries.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

entries.name: schema:validIn
entries.description: The geographic area where the item is valid. Applies for example to a [[Permit]], a [[Certification]], or an [[EducationalOccupationalCredential]].

entries.name: schema:validThrough
entries.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

entries.name: validUntil
entries.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

entries.name: schema:value
entries.description:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

entries.name: schema:valueAddedTaxIncluded
entries.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

entries.name: schema:valueMaxLength
entries.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

entries.name: schema:valueMinLength
entries.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

entries.name: schema:valueName
entries.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

entries.name: schema:valuePattern
entries.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

entries.name: schema:valueReference
entries.description: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

entries.name: schema:valueRequired
entries.description: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

entries.name: schema:variableMeasured
entries.description: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue, or more explicitly as a [[StatisticalVariable]].

entries.name: schema:variantCover
entries.description:
A description of the variant cover
    	for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch
    	Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

entries.name: schema:variesBy
entries.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

entries.name: schema:vatID
entries.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

entries.name: schema:vehicleConfiguration
entries.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

entries.name: schema:vehicleEngine
entries.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

entries.name: schema:vehicleIdentificationNumber
entries.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

entries.name: schema:vehicleInteriorColor
entries.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

entries.name: schema:vehicleInteriorType
entries.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

entries.name: schema:vehicleModelDate
entries.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

entries.name: schema:vehicleSeatingCapacity
entries.description: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

entries.name: schema:vehicleSpecialUsage
entries.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

entries.name: schema:vehicleTransmission
entries.description: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

entries.name: schema:vendor
entries.description: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

entries.name: schema:verificationFactCheckingPolicy
entries.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

entries.name: schema:version
entries.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

entries.name: schema:video
entries.description: An embedded video object.

entries.name: schema:videoFormat
entries.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

entries.name: schema:videoFrameSize
entries.description: The frame size of the video.

entries.name: schema:videoQuality
entries.description: The quality of the video.

entries.name: schema:volumeNumber
entries.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

entries.name: schema:warning
entries.description: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

entries.name: schema:warranty
entries.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

entries.name: schema:warrantyPromise
entries.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

entries.name: schema:warrantyScope
entries.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

entries.name: schema:webCheckinTime
entries.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

entries.name: schema:webFeed
entries.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

entries.name: schema:weight
entries.description: The weight of the product or person.

entries.name: schema:weightPercentage
entries.description: Value in the range [0.0 ; 1.0] representing the fraction of the weight that is used to compute the shipping price.

entries.name: schema:weightTotal
entries.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

entries.name: schema:wheelbase
entries.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet.

entries.name: schema:width
entries.description: The width of the item.

entries.name: schema:winner
entries.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

entries.name: schema:wordCount
entries.description: The number of words in the text of the CreativeWork such as an Article, Book, etc.

entries.name: schema:workExample
entries.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

entries.name: schema:workFeatured
entries.description:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

entries.name: schema:workHours
entries.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

entries.name: schema:workLocation
entries.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

entries.name: schema:workPerformed
entries.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

entries.name: schema:workPresented
entries.description: The movie presented during this event.

entries.name: schema:workTranslation
entries.description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. E.g.  has an English workTranslation Journey to the West, a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese  translation Ty du k bnh kho.

entries.name: schema:workload
entries.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

entries.name: schema:worksFor
entries.description: Organizations that the person works for.

entries.name: schema:worstRating
entries.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system.

entries.name: schema:xpath
entries.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

entries.name: schema:yearBuilt
entries.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

entries.name: schema:yearlyRevenue
entries.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

entries.name: schema:yearsInOperation
entries.description: The age of the business.

entries.name: schema:yield
entries.description: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.
